an><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Mycoplasma pneumonia of swine (MPS) is afairly mild disease of young pigs, however it is considered to be a veryimportant pathogen of pigs. Explain.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">6.</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman, serif;"></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">You have a young foal that has developed avery snotty nose and large swellings under the jaw. Obviously you should callthe vet, but what do you suspect this is and what should you do until the vetcan get out to your farm?<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">7.</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman, serif;"></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Describe the clinical signs, causativeorganisms, and the significance of Atrophic Rhinitis in pigs.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">8.</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman, serif;"></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">You are managing a finishing floor (or are theconsulting veterinarian for one!) and one morning you find several sick pigsthat are not eating, thumping, coughing and exhibiting a fever. By the nextday MANY pigs are very sick and several have died. You do a fie