(26, 'Laura Carraway', 'lcarraway@sampsoncc.edu', 'cphipps@sampsoncc.edu', 'DRE-098-2WA1', '2016-02-02', 1.00, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', '<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>  <o:AllowPNG/> </o:OfficeDocumentSettings></xml><![endif]--><p class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal"><u>Writing AssignmentTwo: Comparison Contrast</u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal">Pick one on the topics below about which to write a 5paragraph essay that compares and/or contrasts.<span style="mso-list:Ignore">v<span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Two similar cars</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2"><span style="mso-list:Ignore">v<span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Two teachers</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2"><span style="mso-list:Ignore">v<span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Two pets you have at home</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2"><span style="mso-list:Ignore">v<span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Two similar occupations</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2"><span style="mso-list:Ignore">v<span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Two similar vacation areas (two beaches or twomountains, etc.)</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo2"><span style="mso-list:Ignore"><span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Once you have picked your topic, brainstorm on asheet of paper to show how the two things are alike and or different. </p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1"><span style="mso-list:Ignore"><span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Once you have your three main points, completean outline for the essay. You can use the sample on Moodle if you need to.</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-left:0in;mso-add-space:auto">RoughDrafts must:</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3"><span style="mso-list:Ignore">2.<span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Be double-spaced</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3"><span style="mso-list:Ignore">4.<span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Have an introduction, thesis, 3 body paragraphs,and a conclusion.</p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3"><span style="mso-list:Ignore">6.<span style="font:7.0pt "Times New Roman""></span>Have the MLA heading information in the top leftcorner.</p><p class="MsoNormal"><br></p><p class="MsoNormal"></p><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> <w:WordDocument>  <w:View>Normal</w:View>  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>  <w:TrackMoves/>  <w:TrackFormatting/>  <w:PunctuationKerning/>  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas/>  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>  <w:DoNotPromoteQF/>  <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>  <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian>  <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript>  <w:Compatibility>   <w:BreakWrappedTables/>   <w:SnapToGridInCell/>   <w:WrapTextWithPunct/>   <w:UseAsianBreakRules/>   <w:DontGrowAutofit/>   <w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark/>   <w:EnableOpenTypeKerning/>   <w:DontFlipMirrorIndents/>   <w:OverrideTableStyleHps/>  </w:Compatibility>  <m:mathPr>   <m:mathFont m:val="Cambria Math"/>   <m:brkBin m:val="before"/>   <m:brkBinSub m:val="--"/>   <m:smallFrac m:val="off"/>   <m:dispDef/>   <m:lMargin m:val="0"/>   <m:rMargin m:val="0"/>   <m:defJc m:val="centerGroup"/>   <m:wrapIndent m:val="1440"/>   <m:intLim m:val="subSup"/>   <m:naryLim m:val="undOvr"/>  </m:mathPr></w:WordDocumen