(27, 'B. Honeycutt', 'bhoneycutt@sampsoncc.edu', 'cphipps@sampsoncc.edu', 'ENG 232 0A', '2016-02-11', 1.50, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', 'on', 1.50, 1.50, 'Students will read William Faulkners biographical information (NAAL pp 695-698) and "Barn Burning" by William Faulkner (NAAL pp 800-812), then watch the short film version of "Barn Burning" linked on Moodle. They will view the powerpoint "Faulkner" linked on Moodle and form preliminary responses to the discussion questions posted therein. Students will be subjected to a quiz covering each of these elements upon my return on 2/16.', '', '', 0.00, '', '', 'other_cause', 'College Transfer Conference at ECU', 'Britt Honeycutt', '2016-02-08', 'Carole Phipps', '2016-02-08', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-02-08'),
(28, 'Jason Frazier', 'jfrazier@sampsoncc.edu', 'cphipps@sampsoncc.edu', 'Eng 112 0D', '2016-02-11', 80.00, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', 'Read "Using Library and Internet Sources", read "Writing Process Notes", Take "Writing Process Quiz"', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, '', '', 'other_cause', 'College Transfer Conference at ECU', 'Jason Frazier', '2016-02-08', 'Carole Phipps', '2016-02-08', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-02-08'),
(29, 'Joy Rogers', 'jrogers@sampsoncc.edu', 'cphipps@sampsoncc.edu', 'COM 231-OA', '2016-02-11', 1.50, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', '<p style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:15.0pt"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica",sans-serif;color:#595959">1-Read through all current notes in Moodle (Power point & LectureNotes)Taking a pen to paper and writing your first speech, SpeechPreparation and Tasks, and Panic Out and Confidence In. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p style="margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; line-height: 15pt;"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica",sans-serif;color:#595959">2-Quiz in Moodle on this assigned reading in Moodle.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style="margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; line-height: 15pt;"><span style="line-height: 15pt;">3-Rehearsing the Speech & Timing the Speech: "Talk itOut" Activity</span><br></p><p style="margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; line-height: 15pt;"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica",sans-serif;color:#595959"><i style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica",sans-serif;color:#595959">Directions: Take the current speech we are working on in the class.<o:p style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica",sans-serif;color:#595959"></o:p></i></span></p><p style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:15.0pt"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica",sans-serif;color:#595959"><i>Begin to talk out your speech aloud using your current outline.Can you do it? Did you stay within the 1-3 minute time limit? You may find thatyou stop to add notes, comments, or things you want to add to your speech. Thetrick is to become familiar with your outline and be able to talk out yourspeech aloud--not to read it. This will help you add or take away informationfrom your speech.<o:p></o:p></i></span></p><p style="margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; line-height: 15pt;"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica",sans-serif;color:#595959"><i>Get with someone to work with you and listen to you. For yourfirst speech, you will not be allowed to read off of your paper. You can havenote cards to help guide you, and having speaking points written on paper insentence form is not suggested. The reason is that you become tempted to readoff of the paper. That can cause you to lose points.<o:p></o:p></i></span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"></p><p style="margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; line-height: 15pt;"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica",sans-serif;color:#595959"><i>Trust me when I say that practice now will help you to become abetter speaker when its time to deliver your speech. Make sure with thisactivity you get a specific time on your speech.</i><o:p></o:p></span></p><p style="margin: 0in 0in 7.5pt; line-height: 15pt;"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Helvetica",sans-serif;color:#595959">4-</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Students will be transferring their main talking points for their speech to note cards.</span></p>', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, '', '', 'other_cause', 'Attending a Transfer Summit at East Carolina University during class time', 'Joy Rogers', '2016-02-08', 'Carole Phipps', '2016-02-08', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-02-08'),
