(37, 'Ria Westphal', 'rwestphal@sampsoncc.edu', 'cphipps@sampsoncc.edu', 'ART 111 OA', '2016-02-15', 1.50, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', '<table class="MsoNormalTable" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"> <tbody><tr>  <td style="padding:2.25pt 2.25pt 2.25pt 2.25pt">  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size:11.5pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif;  mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:#212121">by<a href="http://mymoodle.sampsoncc.edu/user/view.php?id=6403&course=3418" target="_blank"><span style="color:blue;background:#FFEE94">Ria</span><span style="color:blue"><span style="background:#FFEE94">Westphal</span></a>-  Monday, February 15, 2016, 10:06 AM<o:p></o:p></span></p>  </td> </tr> <tr>  <td valign="top" style="padding:2.25pt 2.25pt 2.25pt 2.25pt">  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size:11.5pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif;  mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:#212121"><o:p></o:p></span></p>  </td>  <td style="padding:2.25pt 2.25pt 2.25pt 2.25pt">  <p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size:11.5pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif;  mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";color:#212121">Hello everyone:<o:p></o:p></span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.5pt;  font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";  color:#212121">Please scroll down to<b>Topic 10</b>. <b>Watch the  two M.C. Escher videos</b>. Then<b>review "</b><a href="http://mymoodle.sampsoncc.edu/mod/resource/view.php?id=191755" target="_blank"><b><span style="color:blue">The Structure of Art</span></b></a><b>"  PPT</b>. After that,<b>click on the URL</b>showing you how  to create a<a href="http://mymoodle.sampsoncc.edu/mod/url/view.php?id=203326" target="_blank"><span style="color:blue">Tessellation</span></a>. If you were  absent last class session, or if you do not like your creation, please follow  the directions and<b>create your very own</b><a href="http://mymoodle.sampsoncc.edu/mod/url/view.php?id=203326" target="_blank"><b><span style="color:blue">tessellation</span></b></a>! You  may use a geometric shape or an organic (free form) one. <b>Do not  color your</b><a href="http://mymoodle.sampsoncc.edu/mod/url/view.php?id=203326" target="_blank"><b><span style="color:blue">tessellation</span></b></a><b>yet-that  will be a group project in class.</b><o:p></o:p></span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.5pt;  font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";  color:#212121">In the meantime,<b>decide</b>if you want to go  with<b>black and white</b>(remember the Gestalt psychology  pictures we looked at?) or if you want to use<b>colors</b>for  your<a href="http://mymoodle.sampsoncc.edu/mod/url/view.php?id=203326" target="_blank"><span style="color:blue">tessellation</span></a>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size:11.5pt;  font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";  color:#212121">Please have all this (and all late work s.a. the</span></b><span style="font-size:11.5pt;font-family:"Segoe UI",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:  "Times New Roman";color:#212121"><a href="http://mymoodle.sampsoncc.edu/mod/resource/view.php?id=202774" target="_blank"><b><span style="color:blue">Pop Art</span></b></a><b>selfie)  ready on Wednesday!</b><o:p></o:p></span></p>  </td> </tr></tbody></table>', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, '', '', 'inclement_weather', '', 'Ria Westphal', '2016-02-16', 'Carole Phipps', '2016-02-16', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-02-18'),
(52, 'Sharon Herring', 'sherring@sampsoncc.edu', 'sbaxter@sampsoncc.edu', 'EDU 145 0A', '2016-02-15', 1.50, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', 'on', '', 1.50, 'Students were scheduled to take the Chapter 9 Quiz during class on Feb. 15th. Students are required to complete the quiz and submit no later than midnight on Feb. 17, 2016.', '', 'inclement_weather', '', 'Sharon Herring', '2016-02-16', 'Susan Baxter', '2016-02-17', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-02-18'),
(38, 'Laura Carraway', 'lcarraway@sampsoncc.edu', 'cphipps@sampsoncc.edu', 'DRE-098-1WA1', '2016-02-15', 2.50, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', '<p class="MsoNormal"><b>DRE Writing Assignment----Argumentative<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]-->1.<span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 7pt; "></span><!--[endif]-->Think of something about which you have adefinite opinion. It could be a serious issue like teen pregnancy, smoking,drugs, drunk driving, etc. or anything else you have strong feelings about. Itcould be something less serious like something you enjoy doing or somethingthat really gets on your nerves. Basically, just brainstorm until you find atopic you can write about to convince me to believe the way that you do aboutit. Come up with a thesis, then come up with 3 good reasons to convince me.EVERYTHING MUST BE WRITTEN IN 3<sup>rd</sup> PERSON. For example: Insteadof: I think Skittles are the best fruitcandies because I like how you can hide them in your pocket., you would write,Skittles are the best fruit candies because they can be hidden in ones pocket. It is your opinion, but it is writtenin a way that sounds objective.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>2.<span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 7pt; "> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Afterbrainstorming and narrowing your topic, make a cluster diagram or some othergraphic organizer to organize your thoughts. What will be the main points youwill use to convince me? What supporting details can you use to reinforce thosemain points? <b><u><o:p></o:p></u></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><b><u><o:p><span style="text-decoration:none"></span></o:p></u></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>3.<span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 7pt; "> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Next,make an outline of your ideas in the order you think they would best bepresented to me. You can either type this or write it <u>very neatly</u> inblue or black ink or pencil.<b><u><o:p></o:p></u></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><b><u><o:p><span style="text-decoration:none"></span></o:p></u></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>4.<span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 7pt; "> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Typeyour rough draft in Times New Roman 12 point font and double-space throughout.Set up the spacing BEFORE you type the essay. You should have a title that iscentered and correctly capitalized. You should also have your name, teachername, course name, and date in the upper left corner of the essay. <b>Do not put this in the header section.<u><o:p></o:p></u></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><b><u><o:p><span style="text-decoration:none"></span></o:p></u></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><b><u><o:p><span style="text-decoration:none"></span></o:p></u></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>5.<span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 7pt; "> </span></b><!--[endif]--><b>Rough drafts are due </b><b><u><span style="font-size:18.0pt;line-height:107%">Wed, Feb. 17.</span></u> If they are late, they willautomatically lose 10 points.</b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:"Comic Sans MS"">You arerequired to turn in brainstorm, outline, and rough draft together on Feb 17<sup>th</sup>.<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p>', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, '', '', 'inclement_weather', '', 'Laura G. Carraway', '2016-02-16', 'Carole Phipps', '2016-02-16', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-02-18'),
