(57, 'B. Honeycutt', 'bhoneycutt@sampsoncc.edu', 'cphipps@sampsoncc.edu', 'ENG 111 0A', '2016-02-15', 1.50, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', 'on', 1.50, 0.50, '<p class="MsoNormal"><b>ENG 111 Name:<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><i>Notes before you getstarted:<o:p></o:p></i></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><i>1)<span style="font-style: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></i><!--[endif]--><i>To complete this worksheet, view the powerpoint <b>How to Do Academic Research</b>. Viewit as a slide show so that you can see the animations. Answer the first sectionas you go through the power point.<o:p></o:p></i></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>How to Do AcademicResearch<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><o:p></o:p></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>1.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Whats the first thing you should do when youbegin doing academic research?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>2.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Whatare the two things you can do at the library (according to this power point)?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle">A)<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast">B)<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>3.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Whatdo you click on to access the online library catalogue?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>4.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Whatdo you do if your first search doesnt yield any results?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>5.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Whattype of skills should you use when deciding which search terms to use?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>6.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Toget to NCLive, what page should you start on?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>7.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Willevery article in your results list be relevant to your topic? How will youdetermine if it is relevant?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>8.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Whatis an abstract? Can you use quotes from the abstract in your paper?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left:.25in"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>9.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Whatare the four ways to use the article?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-left:2.5in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-2.0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3"><!--[if !supportLists]-->A)<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"></span><!--[endif]-->C)<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="margin-left:2.5in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-2.0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3"><!--[if !supportLists]-->B)<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"></span><!--[endif]-->D)<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>10.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Howcan you get a correct MLA style citation for this article?<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo2"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>11.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]-->Explainhow to get a copy of an ar