(174, 'Torwanna Coe', 'tcoe@sampsoncc.edu', 'sbaxter@sampsoncc.edu', 'EDU 119 HB', '2016-03-17', 1.25, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', 'on', 1.25, 0.00, '<p>EDU 119 HB2 Make-Up Plan for 3/17/16<o:p></o:p></p><p>Torwanna Coe<o:p></o:p></p><p><b><o:p></o:p></b></p><p><b>Instructions:</b><o:p></o:p></p><p>Each student will make at least a 15 power point slide presentation on whatyour role is as a teacher with children and their play. You can reference theinformationin Chapter 4 and lecture noteson play and the value ofplay to children. <o:p></o:p></p><p>Include graphics of children and/or teachers. For example, you cantalk about your role as a facilitator in the classroom and give examples of howyou would be a facilitator in the classroom. <o:p></o:p></p><p>If you use information on play from the internet or other resources, be sureto site at the bottom of the slide where the information came from.<o:p></o:p></p><p><o:p></o:p></p><p>**Make sure you have atleast 15 slides, at minimum.<o:p></o:p></p><p>**Include graphics to enhance your power point presentation.<o:p></o:p></p><p><o:p></o:p></p><p><b>Assignment Submission:<o:p></o:p></b></p><p>This assignment will be submitted through Moodle by specified date given.<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>', '', '', 0.00, '', '', 'other_cause', 'Out of town education conference ', 'Torwanna Coe', '2016-03-08', 'Susan Baxter', '2016-03-08', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-03-08'),
(176, 'Patricia Welfare', 'pwelfare@sampsoncc.edu', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'ACC131-HB', '2016-02-24', 2.00, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', 'on', 'Complete the Following', 2.00, 'Complete Cengage problems:<p>C4: MC, Prob 1, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 10, 11, 14, 1, 2A</p><p>C5: MC, Prob 2, 3, 5, 8, 9, 11, 14, 16, 17, 21, 1, 2A</p><p>C6: MC, Prob 1, 4, 5, 7, 8, 10, 11, 12, 1, 2A</p>', '', 'inclement_weather', '', 'Patricia Welfare', '2016-03-07', 'W. Darell Matthews', '2016-03-10', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-03-10'),
(177, 'Patricia Welfare', 'pwelfare@sampsoncc.edu', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'ACC226-HB', '2016-02-24', 1.50, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', 'on', 'Multiple Tests', 1.50, 'Complete tests online', '', 'inclement_weather', '', 'Patricia Welfare', '2016-03-07', 'W. Darell Matthews', '2016-03-10', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-03-10'),
(179, 'Michele L. Moore', 'mmoore@sampsoncc.edu', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'SPA141', '2016-02-24', 1.25, '', '0000-00-00', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', '<p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Some of you havent seen all of The Mission, so youll have to wait until you can finish the movie.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><b>The Mission, synopsis</b>Set in the 18th century, Jeremy Irons stars as Father Gabriel, one of several Spanish Jesuit priests assigned to convert the Guaran tribe of South America into Christians. His efforts are gradual, but successful. Converging with this story is Rodrigo Mendoza (Robert De Niro), a slave trader who seeks penance after killing his own brother in a fit of rage. For all the Guaran that he has killed or sold off into slavery, they still show compassion and forgiveness towards him, and he is accepted into the mission, even converting into a Jesuit priest under the guidance of Father Gabriel.<br><br>The priests and the Guaran natives eventually find themselves in heated discussion with politicians and slave-owners, who are debating over whether the mission should fall under the rule of Portugal, thus endangering all the Guaran with the possibility of being made into slaves. Determined to prevent such an action at any cost, Mendoza takes up his sword once more, coming into conflict with Father Gabriels peaceful approach.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><br data-mce-bogus="1"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><b>Historical Facts:</b></p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">1. The Jesuits from Spain, were sent to South America (what is now Paraguay, Argentina, Brazil, Bolivia, and Uruguay) to convert the Indians in to Christians. Unlike other religious missions, their goal was to only spread Christianity and not to civilize the natives. This approach made the missions very successful and profitable.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">2. In 1750, Spain and Portugal signed the Treaty of Madrid. This document concerned their empires and status of their slave plantations in the Americas, mainly in what is now Brazil. The Treaty allowed expansion of the slave holding Portuguese Empire at the expense of the non-slave holding Empire of Spain.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">3. After the signing of the Treaty, the Indians were<b>forced</b>to leave the missions. As we saw in the movie, the Guaran king refused to leave and chose to fight. In 1754, the Guaran tribes alongside some Jesuit priests fought against the Spanish and the Portuguese armies. Unfortunately, the Guaran were outnumbered and lack the appropriate technology to defend their rights.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Your assignment is to submit your MOVIE CRITIQUE:</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><b>Movie Critique</b></p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">1. Did you like the movie?</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">2. Would you recommend it to a friend?</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">3. How would you rate its HISTORICAL ACCURACY" based on what youve read?</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><b>4.</b>Important Quotes</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Below are some important quotes from the movie.<b>Pick one</b>and tell me why it is important to the movie and how you think it relates to what weve discussed and what youve read so far about Latin America.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><b>1.</b> The very last line in the movie:</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">So, your Holiness, now your priests are dead, and I am left alive. But in truth it is I who am dead, and they who live. For as always, your Holiness, the spirit of the dead will survive in the memory of the living.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><b>2.</b>Altamirano (Man from Spain assigned to decide the fate of the Missions)</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Your Holiness, a surgeon to save the body must often hack off a limb. But in truth nothing could prepare me for the beauty and the power of the limb that I had come here to sever.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><b>3.</b>Father Gabriel</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">We are not the members of a democracy, Father. We are the members of an order.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;"><b>5.</b>Father Gabriel vs. Father Rodrigo</p><p style="margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px;">Im curious would you follow the path of Father Gabriel or of Father Rodrigo? Both men were Martyrswhy?</p>', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, '', '', 'inclement_weather', '', 'Michele L. Moore', '2016-03-10', 'W. Darell Matthews', '2016-03-10', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2016-03-10'),
