(411, 'Ria Westphal', 'rwestphal@sampsoncc.edu', 'cphipps@sampsoncc.edu', 'PED 111 OB', '2017-02-23', 1.25, '', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', 'on', 1.25, 1.25, '<p style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:14.4pt;background:#F8F8F8">Students will review a list of 12 lifestyle habits on page 1 of the attached assignment. They will then need to apply their critical thinking skills to answer if they are already making some or all of these habits part of their lifestyle. Students will then suggest changes they could incorporate into their daily lives in order to increase their health.</p><p style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:14.4pt;background:#F8F8F8">Pages 2 - 4 of the assignment consist of the US Governments food guide (choosemyplate.gov), a short column "Balancing the Diet," and the following questions:</p><p style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:14.4pt;background:#F8F8F8"><b><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: Tahoma, sans-serif;">Now visit our cafeteria and listall items on their menu on the attached page.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:14.4pt;background:#F8F8F8"><b><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: Tahoma, sans-serif;">Review what you have learned onfigure 5.4. Now answer the following questions: <o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:.5in;text-indent:-.25in;line-height:14.4pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;background:#F8F8F8"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: Tahoma, sans-serif; font-weight: normal;">-<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: Times New Roman;"> </span></b><!--[endif]--><b><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: Tahoma, sans-serif; font-weight: normal;">-<span style="font-