(422, 'Susan Baxter', 'sbaxter@sampsoncc.edu', 'bstarling@sampsoncc.edu', 'EDU 131 0A', '2017-04-04', 1.50, '', '', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', 'Chapter 13: Working with Families from Diverse Backgrounds<p>Open the Chapter 13 Resource folder in Module Four of our Moodle Course. You will see a video link. Watch the video. </p><p>Next, visithttps://implicit.harvard.edu/implicit/takeatest.html</p><p>After consenting to take the hidden bias inventory, a new screen will open with over 10 inventories. You will select and take two inventories. </p><p>After completing the inventories, you will write a journal entry (prompt provided in Moodle) about the experience. The journal is private between student and instructor and is located in Module 4, directly under the Chapter 13 Resources folder.</p>', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, '', '', 'other_cause', 'Faculty member on a SACSCOC visit', 'Susan Baxter', '2017-03-14', 'Susan Baxter', '2017-03-14', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2017-03-16'),
