(445, 'Billy Kennedy', 'bkennedy@sampsoncc.edu', 'sbaxter@sampsoncc.edu', 'HSE 123 Interviewing Techniquese', '2017-04-06', 1.50, '', '', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', 'Students will be asked to complete two one page written assignments and complete a quiz covering the material from Chapter 12 of our textbook.<p><br></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:" times="" new="" roman",serif"="">Makeup assignment #1<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:" times="" new="" roman",serif"=""><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:" times="" new="" roman",serif"="">It isimportant that beginning clinicians understand how attractions develop in thecourse of intense, intimate, relationally focused work together. <b>Please write a one page summary</b> of thegood reasons, not just the ethics of professional work-focused relationships, butalso the good reasons why work-focused roles have boundaries around them. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Makeup assignment #2<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family:" times="" new="" roman",serif"="">Please write a one page summary</span></b><span style="font-family:" times="" new="" roman",serif"=""> of the factors in a clients lifethat may leave him or her vulnerable to exploitation by a clinician. Thendiscuss the factors in a clinicians life that may lead to exploitation ofclients.</span><o:p></o:p></p><p></p>', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, '', 'Makeup assignment for April 6 2017 .docx', 'other_cause', 'Attending alcohol and drug prevention training in Winston Salem. ', 'B.G. Kennedy', '2017-03-29', 'Susan Baxter', '2017-03-29', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2017-03-29'),
