(464, 'Ria Westphal', 'rwestphal@sampsoncc.edu', 'cphipps@sampsoncc.edu', 'ART 111 OA', '2017-05-01', 1.25, '', '', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', '<p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_609" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><span id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_619" style="font-size: xx-large;"><b id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_618" style="line-height: 1.4;">Frida Kahlo & Auguste Rodin</b></span></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_622" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><br><img src="http://studiorue-blog.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Frida-Kahlo.jpg" width="150" height="225" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_621" style="vertical-align: middle; border: 0px;"></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_644" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">"I never paint dreams or nightmares. I paint my own reality."<span id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_643" style="line-height: 1.4;">- Frida Kahlo</span></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_645" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><b>RIGHT CLICK THE LINK BELOW & OPEN IN NEW TAB</b></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_626" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><b id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_625"><span id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_624" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"><iframe width="480" height="270" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/lnFM04Lv_U4?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_623"></iframe></span></b></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_628" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><span id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_627" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">This is the story of the artist Frida Kahlo. She was quite a risque lady whos artwork was seemingly strange, but perfect for what she was trying to say. Her life was quite interesting... full of ups and downs. Even though she was female, she is just as shocking as some of her male colleagues. The video biography was produced by high schoolers, so a bit of the information is "off" however, they got all of the "big stuff" correct! I think this little video is humorous... and a good platform for you to decide if you want to do more research about Frida. (15 mins)</span></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_629" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">***********************************************************************************************************</p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_630" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/95/Auguste_Rodin_fotografato_da_Nadar_nel_1891.jpg" width="150" style="vertical-align: middle; border: 0px;"><br>"To the artist there is never anything ugly in nature."- Auguste Rodin</p><p style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><b>RIGHT CLICK & OPEN IN NEW TAB</b></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><a href="http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x1gbuou_biography-of-auguste-rodin-discovery-history-art-documentary_creation" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(0, 39, 76); text-decoration: none; -webkit-transition: all 0.3s; transition: all 0.3s;"><b><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x1gbuou_biography-of-auguste-rodin-discovery-history-art-documentary_creation</span></b></a></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_631" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">This Video highlights the artist Auguste Rodin. He was an extremely famous sculptor. Some of his sculptures are actually on display at the North Carolina Museum Of Art. One of Rodins most famous & controversial works was "The Kiss". At first glance you are going to wonder what direction the class is going! However, put on your grown up pants and learn to appreciate this sculpture for what it is.... absolute beauty. Some of you may get a giggle, many of you will see its grandeur... but in the end you should realize what exactly you are looking at: One of the most famous sculptures of all time! (48 mins)</p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_632" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">I must warn you... there is NUDITY (it is everywhere in art!) and reference to "naughty" things. Try your best to keep it together. You probably do not want to watch this in public or around small children.</p><p style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">If you start the movie and find it offensive, you do not have to watch it. There will be questions from the video on your exam, but there will not be enough of them to KILL your grade if you study every thing else.</p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_635" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><span id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_633">************************************************************************************************************</span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="font-size: large;"><b>The 4 Stages of Art Criticism</b></span></em></span></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_636" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><b>RIGHT CLICK & OPEN IN NEW TAB</b></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_638" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><iframe width="480" height="270" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fz-sUb3E_C8?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_637"></iframe></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_640" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><span id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_639" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">This is a short 3 minute video of random people Critiquing a piece of art by the Street Artist named "Banksy". You will notice that they are NOT using the "4 stages of Art Criticism" simply because, "everyday people" dont go through the Formal Process.... The video will give you some insight on how you critique things all the time, and you dont even realize it!.... but yes, you do need to at least know what the 4 Stages are, so Please look at the power point!--- There will be questions on the Exam!<img class="emoticon" alt="smile" title="smile" src="https://mymoodle.sampsoncc.edu/theme/image.php/altitude/core/1492779936/s/smiley" style="vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 15px; height: 15px;"></span></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);">************************************************************************************************************</p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_642" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><b id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_641">You will be asked to complete a discussion forum on this topic.</b></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><b>*Please be respectful of others and be mindful when making postsabout this videos!*</b></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_652" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><b>Be sure to look at the powerpoint below!</b></p><p id="yui_3_17_2_1_1493058360157_651" style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><b>You will need it for the forum and your Exam.<img class="emoticon" alt="smile" title="smile" src="https://mymoodle.sampsoncc.edu/theme/image.php/altitude/core/1492779936/s/smiley" style="vertical-align: middle; border: 0px; width: 15px; height: 15px;"></b></p><p style="margin-bottom: 1em; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; font-family: Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.2000007629395px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><b></b></p>', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, '', 'The Problems of Art Criticism.docx Make-Up May 1 2017.docx', 'other_cause', 'Personal Day', 'Ria Westphal', '2017-04-24', 'Carole Phipps', '2017-04-24', 'William J. Starling (aw)', '2017-04-24'),
(465, 'B.G. Kennedy', 'bkennedy@sampsoncc.edu', 'sbaxter@sampsoncc.edu', 'HSE 125 Counseling', '2017-05-02', 1.50, '', '', 0.00, 0.00, 'on', '<blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><font face="Open Sans, Tahoma, Geneva, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; background-color: rgb(248, 248, 248);"><br>Share some of the most important things that you have learned about counseling this semester. Describe how it is like and unlike what you expected. What did you discover about the profession? Explain your answer fully in a 1-2 page summary.&nbsp;</span></font></blockquote>', '', 0.00, 0.00, '', '', '', 0.00, '', '', 'other_cause', 'Community leave', 'B.G. Kennedy', '2017-04-26', '', '0000-00-00', '', '0000-00-00');
