n path.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes"> </span>I am studying for the CCNP Switch exam andintend to take it in the spring. </span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">3.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes"> </span>I will complete much more that the 15 hoursrequired for professional development in preparation for the CCNP exam.</span></u></p>', 'Al Spraker', 'W. Darell Matthews');
INSERT INTO `perfobj1` (`ID`, `employee`, `date_submitted`, `obj_setting_period`, `supervisor`, `section_1`, `section_2`, `employee_signature`, `supervisor_signature`) VALUES
(29, 'Rebecca Scott', '2016-08-25', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Goal 1 Objective 1.5 Foster academic excellence by assessing student needs and outcomes. Improve teaching performance by promoting learning opportunities and student engagement through interactive class and lab activities to help student succeed.<p><br></p><p>2. Goal 1 Objective 4 Maintain student records per guidelines of Division of Health Services Regulations.</p><p><br></p><p>3. Goal 5 Implement State mandated Nurse Aide curriculum to prepare student to enter workforce.</p>', '1. Model life long learning by attending professional development workshops.<p><br></p><p>2. Attend regional Nurse Aide workshops and meetings to remain updated on Nurse Aide curriculum .</p><p><br></p><p>3. Attend Community College Conference this fall.</p><p><br></p><p>4. Meet compliance for CEU necessary for renewal of RN license for NCBON.</p>', 'Rebecca Scott', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(30, 'Alisha F. Carwise', '2016-08-25', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'Objective 1.1 Improve student goal completion and graduation rates by informing students about various activities and encouraging participation. The activities will increase the knowledge base, improve test taking skills, increase comfort level with course material and establish a rapport between instructor and student.<p><br></p><p>Objective 1.4 Expand opportunities for student engagement with faculty and staff. Increased office hours by appointment will be announced to class for any questions or concerns as well as contact electronically utilizing distance education technologies and modalities.</p><p><br></p><p>Objective 4.1 Document student attainment of learning outcomes by serving on the curriculum systematic program evaluation plan nursing committee.</p>', 'I will complete the curriculum development graduate course at East Carolina University in order to enhance student learning and increase knowledge ofcontemporary issues related to curriculum development in nursing education.<p>I will continue to work as a registered nurse at an acute care facility in order to remain current on technology and practices related to nursing/healthcare to enrich student learning.</p><p>A moodle certification course will be attended in order to enhance blended learning capabilities.</p>', 'Alisha F. Carwise, RN', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(31, 'Kristina C. Edwards', '2016-08-22', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<p>Goal 1; Objective 1.1 -- Improve student goal completion and graduation rates. I plan toencourage student participation intest-taking workshopsto improve retention in the Practical Nursing program.</p><p>Goal 1; Objective 1.4 -- Expand opportunities for student engagement with staff and faculty. I plan to maintain an approachable attitude with students and provide students with ample opportunities to come to my office for assistance or questions. Additionally, I plan to increase one-on-one conferences with students regarding test performance to help develop knowledge base and test taking skills. </p><p>Goal 4; Objective 4.3 -- Improve access to student and institutional data in support of decision making. I plan to encourage student participation in faculty and student government meetings to promote student involvement. </p><p><br></p>', 'I plan to continue my nursing competence via continuing education opportunities and practicing within the clinical setting. I also will attend the North Carolina Community College Systems Pathways to Success conference in October 2016. I am also planning to attend Moodle training to become certified in Moodle and test-writing workshops as available. ', 'Kristina C. Edwards', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(32, 'Loreta M. Jones', '2016-08-25', '2016-2017', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Advising and recruit students during registration, NSO, Open House, and college career days and tours.<p>2. Administer effective record-keeping for the college and NC State Board of Cosmetic Arts.</p><p>3. Build an effective communication through educator-to-educator- to-supervisor relationship.</p><p>4. Delivering outstanding customer service</p><p>5. Delivering the new State Exam for Cosmetology</p>', '1. Up-date licenses for Cosmetology and CEUS for renewal of cosmetology license and gain new material and skill for cosmetology instructor.<p>2. Attend the NCCCCS in October.</p><p>3. Attend the NCCCCIA for Cosmetology Instructors</p><p>4. Achieve a Batchelors in Biblical Studies.</p><p><br></p>', 'Loreta M. Jones', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
