(35, 'Veronica F. Stevens', '2016-08-26', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<span style="font-size:20px;">1. Assess student needs and outcomes to develop relevant learning opportunities (Goal 4, Objective 4.1)</span><p><span style="font-size:20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-size:20px;">2. Increase student retention through advising, counseling, effective teaching, and specific retention strategies (Goal 1, Objective 1.1).</span></p><p><span style="font-size:20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-size:20px;">3. Make improvements and revisions to distance learning curriculum (Goal 2, Objective 2.3).</span></p><p><span style="font-size:20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-size:20px;">4. Collect and maintain data to maintain ACEN accreditation (Goal 4).</span></p>', '<span style="font-size:20px;">I would like to engage in continuing education regarding distance learning. I would like to enhance skills and knowledge relative to advanced practice nursing.</span>', 'Dr. Veronica F. Stevens', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(36, 'Lauren Cochran', '2016-08-26', '2016-2017', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'One of my objectives is to obtain the graduate credit hours needed to teach Economic courses for the college. I have to take approximately 3-4 additional economic classes to have the necessary 18 credit hours. I plan to take at least one course this spring, possibly more depending on the type of class (5 week vs 16 week). I also want to become more knowledgeable about Moodle. I think this will be helpful for me to learn and become comfortable with all the features available for the different types of classes I am teaching: hybrid, online, and face to face. ', 'I plan to attend the training on October 10-11 in Raleigh. This semester, I also plan on finding the school and courses I can take to fulfill my economic graduate hours and enroll for spring classes. I also want to participate in any workshops, seminars, or other activities that I find to help me with my teaching.', 'Lauren Cochran', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(37, 'Barney Grady', '2016-08-26', '2016-2017', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Develop first web course for the BCT program in an effort to make the program available to more students.<p><br></p><p>2. Develop new Career and College Promise Diploma to make more classes in the program available to high school students.</p><p><br></p><p><br><p><br></p><p><br></p></p>', '1. Attend the NCCCS 2016 Conference to help with program improvements.<p><br></p><p>2. Research 8 week web and hybrid courses to help meet the growing need. This is an area that has seen growth in recent years for BCT programs around the state and I feel we could see the same thing for our program. To keep the program on its current growth pattern multiple delivery options are almost a must.</p><p><br></p>', 'Barney Grady', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(38, 'Sabrina Pope ', '2016-08-26', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Increase student retention through quality counseling, advising, and instruction (Goal 1. Objective 1.1)<p><br><p>2. Develop innovative learning opportunities to assess students and improve student outcomes (Goal 1, Objective 1.5)</p><p><br></p><p>3. Expand opportunities for student engagement with staff and faculty (Goal 1, Objective 4.3)</p><p><br></p><p>4. Participate in assessments to identify and meet community needs to promote open access to the college (Goal 3, Objective 3.3)</p><p><br></p><p>5. Collect data to maintain ACEN accreditation (Goal 4, Objective 4.2)</p></p>', '<span style="font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">I will continue my professional and personaldevelopment by attending and participating in learning activities, such asavailable workshops and seminars. I will continue to participate on campus anddepartment committees as well as any community committees. Additionally, I willcontinue my professional and personal development by working closely with thementors in the nursing department.</span>', 'Sabrina Vanessa Pope ', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
