(43, 'Jennifer Wiley', '2015-08-13', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoNormal">Successfully complete General Instructor School atFayetteville Technical Community College <o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Successfully complete the BLET School Directors ConferenceSeptember 2015<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Successfully complete the Leadership Summit and Workshop atNorth Carolina State University November 20, 2015<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Learn requirements and management of the BLET program inorder to facilitate the September 2015 BLET cadets class as Director of BasicLaw Enforcement Training<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Maintain oversight of the criminal justice academicdepartment as Criminal Justice Chair and successfully facilitate 18 credithours <o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Attend community functions (as available) to promote SCC andgrow enrollment in Criminal Justice and BLET throughout the academic year<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Facilitate the Academic Advisory Board Meeting for CriminalJustice for the 2015-2016 academic year<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Maintain working relationship with the local criminaljustice agencies in order to gain information about the recent procedures andtechnology in the field to be incorporated into the classroom. <o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">Continue as advisor to the SCC Criminal Justice Cluband document/support activities of the club that serve the community</span>', '<p class="MsoNormal">Successfully complete Gener