(44, 'Al Spraker', '2015-08-22', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">1. We are offering two new courses this falland are also new in the CCNA Curriculum.Both courses are being taught through the Cisco Network Academy(NetAcad). NET 225 the first 8 weeksthen NET 226 the second eight weeks.Both course cover material included in the new CCNA exam. The courseswill be a challenge for the students especially as an 8 week course.<o:p></o:p></span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">2. With being short an instructor this fall, Iam doing virtually all the advising. Iintend to make it as customer centered as possible. We are also starting a new checklist for ourprograms which requires most of the students to transfer to the newchecklist. I will start getting them alltransferred over in the next few weeks<o:p></o:p></span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">3. I will continue to worked to better utilize thenew features of Moodle. Most of theclasses are Web Assisted or Hybrid and will require the students and me toutilize the platform more effectively.<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black">1. Complete 15 hours ofprofessional development webinars or other online training sessions. I will continue using the many coursesoffered by Cisco through the Network Academy<o:p></o:p></span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">2. I will begin studying and preparing for theCCNA R/S exam. The new courses offeredthis fall will be an helpful.<o:p></o:p></span></u></p>', 'Al Spraker', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(45, 'Nathan McKee', '2016-01-25', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoBodyText2">1. Teach the CTS 120 Hardware/Software Support coursethis Spring, adding and/or modifying courseware in order to ensure students areproperly trained. <o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoBodyText2">2. Teach the SEC 110 Security Concepts course this Springto ensure that students are prepared for the follow-on SEC 150 SecureCommunications course. <o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoBodyText2">3. Teach the SEC 289 Security Capstone Project with AlSpraker in order to ensure students have the skills needed to competesuccessfully in todays Information Systems job market.<o:p></o:p></p><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA;layout-grid-mode:line">4. Teach the NOS 130Windows Single User course this Spring to ensure that students are prepared forthe follow-on NOS 230 Windows Admin course.</span>', '<p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">1.Complete the CompTIA Security+ (SY0-401) coursework through Pluralsight.com<o:p></o:p></span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">2.Prepare for and successfully pass the CompTIA Security+ exam<o:p></o:p></span></u></p><u><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA;layout-grid-mode:line">3. Begin coursework toobtain the Certified Cisco Systems Instructor certification via online courseattendance.</span></u>', 'Nathan McKee', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(46, 'Durwood King', '2015-08-31', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '	To develop and administer the Electrical III program of study in order to better prepare the industrial maintenance workers to maintain the new equipment in the industry\r\n	To complete 2 assessments at Butterball LLC within a 12 month timeframe\r\n	To stay abreast & updated on the new production equipment in business/industry in order to provide ongoing workforce training initiatives\r\n	To network continuously with Sampson Countys business/industry & workforce to enhance the Industrial Maintenance Mechanics & Industrial Ammonia Refrigeration Program of Study(s)\r\n	To provide a safe and healthy classroom & lab environment that promotes student learning & success\r\n	To expand the hands-on labs for ELC-128 (Intro to PLCs) to include new automation training equipment in order to give students a more complete understanding and prepare them for newer equipment being used in industry. We are in process of developing equipment list. A grant will be written by September 30, 2015 to request funding. \r\n	Provide students with skills & knowledge as required by course SLOs\r\n', '	To attend an 8 hour Continuing Education course on National Electrical Code for license renewal\r\n	Meet 15 hours professional and personal training (8 hours will be National Electric Code Class)\r\n', 'Durwood King', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
