h of thisyear in order to complete the Adult ABE Specialty Credentials in Mathand Science.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="margin-left:.75in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>4.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></b><!--[endif]--><b>&nbsp;Continue to attend on-going facultymeetings, staff development meetings and workshops as needed.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</b><b><o:p></o:p></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><sup><span style="font-size:14.0pt;line-height:107%;mso-bidi-font-family:Aharoni">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></sup></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size:14.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Aharoni"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="margin-left:.75in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><span style="font-size: 16px; text-indent: -0.25in;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><br></p>', '', '', 'Sheron C. Jones', ''),
(8, 'Sheron C Jones', '2016-01-07', '2015-2016', 'ctaylor@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:5.25pt;margin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in"><b><sup><span style="font-size:16px;color: black; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin: 0in 0in 5.25pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 16px;"><b style="font-size: 16px;"><sup style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="color: black; font-size: 16px; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We completed an initial assessment&nbsp;in order toeffectively<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px;">&nbsp;place students within theireducational functioning level.&nbsp;&nbsp;We&nbsp;enhanced our academic lessonswith technology, by using the Smart Board and the Computer Lab to integrate contextualizedlessons which incorporated the students interests and strengths. </span><o:p style="font-size: 16px;"></o:p></span></sup></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin: 0in 0in 5.25pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 16px;"><b style="font-size: 16px;"><sup style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 16px; color: black; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">2.<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="apple-converted-space" style="font-size: 16px;">&nbsp;We explored the students natural talents andstrengths through the use of self-assessment activities such as the </span>Myers-BriggsType Indicator and interest profiler.&nbsp;This assessment indicated their primary and secondary career interest.&nbsp; We explored the different programs offeredhere at S.C.C. with associate degrees, diplomas and certificates. This led intoa research project, in which the students discovered careers that wereattainable locally.&nbsp; They visited localbusiness </span>that were associated with their area of interest, where theyattained valuable information in their field of interest.&nbsp; They utilized the US Bureau of LaborStatistics website as a resource for job outlooks, pay, educationalrequirements, work environment, and duties, etc. &nbsp;They culminated their project by creatingposters with data, graphs, charts, and an informative essay which illuminatingwhat they had learned in their job research.&nbsp;The students ended their research with an oral presentation to theclass. <o:p style="font-size: 16px;"></o:p></span></sup></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin: 0in 0in 5.25pt; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 16px;"><b style="font-size: 16px;"><sup style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 16px; color: black; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">3.<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 16px;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="apple-converted-space" style="font-size: 16px;">&nbsp;</span>The majority of my students had an </span>increasein their EFL levels and my student retention rates continue to climb.&nbsp; My RD/ENG class had over 1,300 hours.</span></sup></b></p></span><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:5.25pt;margin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in"><b><sup><span style="font-size: 18pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><o:p></o:p></span></sup></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:5.25pt;margin-left:0in;text-indent:-.25in"></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:5.25pt;margin-left:0in"><b><sup><span style="font-size: 18pt; color: black; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><u1:p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 18px;">&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size:12px;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">&nbsp;</span></u1:p></span></sup></b><b><sup><span style="font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;"><o:p></o:p></span></sup></b></p>', '', '<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="margin-left:.75in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>1.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></b><!--[endif]--><b>&nbsp;Ihave completed the NC Adult Education Core Instructional Credentials and the AdultSecondary Education Certificate and the Specialty Education Certificates in Readingand Social Studies. I also have a NC Reading Specialty Certificate.<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-left:.75in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>2.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></b><!--[endif]--><b>ASE MA 01:Algebraic Concepts andExpressions &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CPCC&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;9/18/2016</b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="margin-left:.75in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>3.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></b><!--[endif]--><b>&nbsp;</b><b>I will attend Adult BasicEducation classes from ABSPD through ASU, in order to complete my ABE SpecialtyCredentials in Math and Science.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ihave one science and two math classes scheduled for January and March of thisyear in order to complete the Adult ABE Specialty Credentials in Mathand Science.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="margin-left:.75in;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><b>4.<span style="font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></b><!--[endif]--><b>&nbsp;Continue to attend on-going facultymeetings, staff development meetings and workshops as needed. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</b><b><o:p></o:p></b></p>', '', '', 'Sheron C. Jones', ''),
(9, 'Nydia Negron-Lopez', '2016-01-08', '2015-2016', 'ctaylor@sampsoncc.edu', 'As the year goes by I am still learning about the WIOA program and how the program help our students. I am also compiling information to start updating the ESL Syllabus and Outline so they can match or correlate with what the instructors are teaching in the classroom and with the LEIS forms and students progress.', '', 'I have attended the following worshops/trainings/webinars:<p><br><p>08/06/15 WIOA Summit, Greenville, NC ;</p><p>08/10/15-College Staff/Faculty Customer Service Worshop 9-10 am,</p><p>08/26/15-WIOA Webinar 2:30-3:00pm</p><p>10/02/15-Workshop SCC O-140 room 9am-12:30</p><p>10/02/15-Workshop Lesson Planning Using Context Standards, Nancy Guy 9am-12</p><p>10/16/15-Basic Skills Instructors/Staff Career Clusters meeting 11pm-12 noon</p><p>10/23/15-ESOL 05 WOrkshop, Wake Tech CC 8am-4:00pm</p><p>11/19/15-Attended Latino Day at Clinton High School, 6pm-8pm</p><p>12/11/15- Integrating Career Awareness into ABE, ASE, And ESl Classroom Workshop, Fayetteville CC, 8am-4pm</p></p>', '', '', 'Nydia Negron Lopez', ''),
(10, 'Amanda J. Raynor', '2016-01-08', '2015-2016', 'abutler@sampsoncc.edu', '<ul><li>I continue to to process contracts for the Small Business Center seminars and acquire the signatures and process through the Business Office.<br></li><li>I continue to process payroll for the Occupational, Contractual, Self-Supporting, Defensive Driving classes and Small Business Seminars.</li><li>I continue to register classes when needed for the Continuing Education and the Small Business Center and I process the registration paperwork once registered.</li><li>Amanda Bradshaw and I continue to meet with Don Spry and other speakers to improve and update the Small Business Center.</li><li>I continue to maintain the Clinton-Sampson Chamber of Commerce website for the Continuing Education and Small Business Center classes/seminars we offer.</li><li>I continue to maintain the Client management System to enter the Small Business Center clients, seminar and register attendees.</li><li>I continue to maintain and create the weekly Constant Contact emails to advertise the upcoming seminars for the Small Business Center.</li></ul>', 'Amanda, I revise my earlier comments upon deeper consideration. &nbsp;You are indeed a superb support person for Aleta and Amanda and a welcoming face and voice to people who call or visit Con Ed. &nbsp;The administrative responsibilities you handle at time bring challenges because of the multiple interruptions you experience at the front desk. &nbsp;Offer me suggestions as to how we can help minimize the distractions that affect your ability to give uninterrupted focus to important, time-sensitive tasks. &nbsp; Do you need scheduled time-out from the front desk to have access to a work area thats quiet? What will help you most? &nbsp; I want your ideas.<p><br></p><p>I do remind you that your front-and-center location makes you highly visible and thus the focus of lots of attention. I trust you to exercise good judgment regarding your time and activities.</p>', '<ul><li>In the Fall 2015 Semester I took Spanish 1 and passed with a A. That completes my requirements for the admission to North Carolina Wesleyan College to complete my bachelors degree.</li><li>I have over 8 hours of Professional Development for the year 2015-2016.</li></ul>', 'Outstanding. &nbsp;I look forward to seeing what career path you choose. &nbsp;You possess many exceptional qualities and leadership potential that I hope your educational pursuits will further cultivate. Your exceptional people skills and intuitive understanding of peoples behavior and motives lend themselves to some promising career opportunities. You owe it to yourself to be all you can be.<p><br></p><p>I appreciate you and all that you contribute to the department both personally and professionally.</p>', '', 'Amanda J. Raynor', 'Ann B. Butler');
