anguage:AR-SA">I participated in the campus workshop CustomerService Training on August 10, 2015.<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA"> </span>Icontinue to participate in department committee and faculty meetings asassigned.<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA"> </span>I attended the annual NCNAConvention in October 2015 and earned 13.5 CEUs.<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA"> </span>I also attended the DNP Council meetingNovember 6, 2015 and earned 1 CEU on the topic Mentee or Mentor: Mastering theAbility to Guide and Follow. I remain a full-time student in the DNP programat Gardner-Webb University, maintaining a 4.0 GPA, with a tentative graduationdate of May 2016.<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA"> </span>I implemented my DNP CapstoneProject during fall semester 2015.<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA"> </span>This projectinvolved incorporation of concept maps as a teaching method with first-year ADNstudents to enhance critical thinking development.<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA"> </span>I am in the process of compiling data and planto defend my DNP presentation April 21, 2016 at Gardner-Webb University.</span>', 'Agree with comments.&nbsp;', 'Mrs. Smith is a dependable and motivated employee who loves what she does and the impact it can have on students.. &nbsp;Her Fall 2015 evaluations were above average in ratings and comments where positive, supporting her excellent performance as a faculty member and employee for SCC. &nbsp;', 'Lisa S. Smith', 'Wanda H. Capps ');
INSERT INTO `perfobj2` (`ID`, `employee`, `date_submitted`, `obj_setting_period`, `supervisor`, `section_1_employee`, `section_1_supervisor`, `section_2_employee`, `section_2_supervisor`, `evaluation_summary`, `employee_signature`, `supervisor_signature`) VALUES
(12, 'Donald Jacobs', '2016-01-11', '2015-2016', 'abutler@sampsoncc.edu', 'Continue using the Smart board to assist students with moving one EFL during this school year.<p>Continue working towards increasing EFLs by 12% during this school year.</p><p>Learning more about the available resources and placement for students that cant benefit educationally from the ACE program.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Attended all training and webinars provided by the state and SCC.<p>Currently enrolled in my last two graduate classes at Liberty University.</p>', '', '', 'Donald JACOBS', ''),
(13, 'Rebecca Scott', '2016-01-12', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. A variety of teaching styles were implemented to promote learning opportunities and promote student engagement .<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">2. Student records were maintained per Division of Health Services Regulations guidelines.</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">3. Nurse Aide I curriculum was implemented per guidelines of Division of Health Services Regulations.</span></p>', 'Mrs. Scott has satisfactorily met her objectives or is continuing to meet them as stated. &nbsp;Agree with her comments. &nbsp;She is detailed in her reports and records and completes them in a timely and orderly manner. &nbsp;She stays abreast of changes in the statewide curriculum and implements changes as required.&nbsp;', 'Attended workshop offered by Division of Health Services Regulations to remain updated on changes in Nurse Aide I program. Read updates received via e-mail from regional consultant regarding changes in Nurse Aide I program.', 'Agree with Mrs. Scotts comments.&nbsp;', '&nbsp;Mrs, Scott is a dedicated employee. &nbsp;One who is always present, always early to work and willing to help with the needs of the nursing department. &nbsp;She attends professional development workshops and continuing education events to maintain her licensure and expertise as an instructor.&nbsp;', 'Rebecca Scott R.N.', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(14, 'Sabrina Pope ', '2016-01-12', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<ol><li><b>Increase student retention through quality counseling, advising, and instruction (Goal 1, Objective 1.1)</b></li><li><b>Participate with development of opportunities for students to participate in service learning (Goal 3, Objective 3.1)</b></li><li><b>Promote academic excellence and expand the opportunity for student engagement with staff and faculty. (Goal 1, Objective 1.4)</li><li><b>Participate in assessments to identify and meet community needs to promote open access to the college (Goal 3, Objective 3.3</b></li><li><b>Collect data to maintain ACEN accreditation (Goal 4).</li></ol><p><p><br></p></p>', 'Mrs. Pope is working toward completing the above objectives. &nbsp;She is being mentored in advising and counseling during registration times as a new employee and has been able to actually advise on her own. &nbsp;She is focused on the students and ensures they have opportunities in the clinical setting to prepare them for nursing. &nbsp;She is learning the ropes of accreditation , the process and documentation required.', '<b>I will enhance my professional and personal development by attending and participating in learning activities such as available workshops and seminars. I will participate in campus and department committees as assigned as well as any community committees. Additionally, I will continue as a full-time student in the MSN program at University of Phoenix, with a tentative graduation date of May 2016.</b>', 'Mrs. Pope has attended the workshops offered her on campus and is currently enrolled in a graduate program with a graduation date of May 2016. &nbsp;', 'Mrs. Pope truly loves what she is doing and it is evident in her daily actions not only with students but with faculty members as well. &nbsp;She is a team player, ready to jump in and assist anyone as needed within the department. &nbsp;She is willing and eager to learn the aspects of teaching within the clinical and didactic setting. &nbsp;She is professional in her interactions and is dependable and focused.&nbsp;<p><br></p>', 'Sabrina Vanessa Pope, BSN, RN', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(15, 'Regina Burgin', '2016-01-12', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'I believe that I am making progress with my personal performance objectives this academic year through quality instruction and advising students. I collect student learning outcome data each semester and I continue to collect and update data for our nursing departments ACEN accreditation. I have also been actively helping students register with our new WebAdvisor process.', 'Agree with Mrs. Burgins comments. &nbsp;Performance objectives as stated are being met satisfactorily. &nbsp;', 'I continue to develop my professional nursing skills by working part-time in an acute care hospital as a staff RN. I also keep abreast of current trends in healthcare through continuing education credits and have completed 6.3 hours as of July 2015. There was no money in the budget for me to attend an ACEN conference in September 2015. However, I did complete the Moodle Certification Course offered at SCC in September, in order to learn more about a program that is used heavily in my instructional courses.', 'Again, agree with Mrs. Burgins comments. &nbsp;She is dedicated to maintaining her knowledge and expertise to better prepare students for the workforce of nursing.&nbsp;', 'Mrs. Burgin is dependable and motivated in performing her instructional duties. &nbsp;She works hard to engage the student both in the classroom and the clinical setting to prepare a safe practitioner. &nbsp;She has a passion and love for nursing that she emulates to her students.&nbsp;', 'Regina Burgin', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(16, 'Krystle Edge', '2016-01-12', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. I met objective 1.3 of increasing my knowledge on advising students in selecting an appropriate course schedule. I was paired with Laura Gray RN on January 5 2016 for student registration. We used the SCC course catalog and advised students on which classes would be good for them to take according to their past classes and their goal completion.<hr id="null">2. I met objective 4.1 of participating in and learning the process for collecting data for the assessment of learning outcomes. I received course work done by both groups of ADN students and graded it with appropriate feedback. I helped with the collection of information related to student learning outcomes.<p><hr id="null">3. I met objective 4.1 of collection of data to maintain ACEN accreditation. I help my fellow faculty with the collection of organization of data needed to maintain ACEN accreditation.</p><p><hr id="null">4. I met objective 1.1 of fostering student goal completion and promoting improved graduation and retention rates through quality instruction. I led a group of students in various clinical and community sites. I counseled students on skills to help in their completion of the nursing program, as well as ways for them to complete further educational goals (i.e. getting their BSN).<p></p></p>', 'Agree with Mrs. Edges comments and evaluation. &nbsp;She is transitioning into the role of a nurse faculty member and is meeting the objectives satisfactorily as stated. &nbsp;', 'I am currently enrolled at East Carolina University in the Nursing Education program an anticipated graduation in May 2017 with my Masters degree. I am also keeping my NCC certification in in-patient obstetrics current along with my other certifications (ACLS, BCLS, NRP, Fetal monitoring, and childbirth education). I also plan to attend the workshop offered in April. I have participated in the committees that I have been assigned.', 'Agree with comments. &nbsp;Mrs. Edge attends workshop and conferences to maintain licensure and is currently a graduate student in the nursing education curriculum.&nbsp;', 'Mrs. Edge is a dependable and eager to learn employee. She is also willing to help any level or division within the nursing department when needed. &nbsp;She is a positive person and a great addition to the nursing faculty as a whole.&nbsp;', 'Krystle Edge', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(17, 'Wanda H Capps', '2016-01-12', '2015-2016', 'bstarling@sampsoncc.edu', 'All performance objectives have been met or are in progress. &nbsp;All ACEN documentation reports have been submitted for the year. &nbsp;I am currently preparing for a focused visit for the LPN to ADN online option implemented Fall 2015. &nbsp;Data is continually collected and evaluated to make program decisions and changes. &nbsp;The Medical Assistant application has been completed to be submitted to NCCCS. &nbsp;The process for identification of RIBN students has been restructure to better track students interested in that pathway. &nbsp;I continue to foster a positive working environment.&nbsp;<p><br></p>', '', 'I have served as an ACEN evaluator at 2 different sites during the 2015 year. &nbsp;I have continued to attend the ADN Directors meetings a well as the Deans of Health Sciences meetings. I attend workshops, conferences and complete continuing education units in order to maintain licensure for subsequent renewal in 2017. &nbsp;I continue to serve as a committee member for the Sampson County Child Fatality Prevention Team. &nbsp;I also attended the SACSCOC summer insitute.&nbsp;', '', '', 'Wanda H. Capps', ''),
(18, 'Laura O Gray', '2016-01-14', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<p>1-Obj 1.4: This objective has been partially met. I attended the freshman welcome luncheon and plan to also attend the senior graduation luncheon and pinning ceremony.<p>2-Obj 8.1: I have done some searching for grants related to nursing educaiton but have not completed this objective.</p><p>3-Obj 1.1: I continue to particiapte in student advising and counseling. I am continually seeking ways to improve effective teaching.</p><p>4-Obj. 4.1 and 4.3: I am continually assisting in maintaining documentation and data for ACEN accreditation.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p></p>', 'Agree with Mrs. Grays comments. &nbsp;She has met or is working toward meeting her performance objectives she set for the academic year. &nbsp;No areas of concern noted.&nbsp;', '<p>1-I began but did not complete the moodle certification but plan to look for other moodle learning opportunites this year.</p><p>2-I no longer work part time at Sampson Regional Medical Center. I do complete various Medscape type CEU opportunites to maintain current evidence based practice knowledge.</p><p>3-I continue to serve on a Roseboro NC-STEP committee.</p><p><br></p>', 'Agree.....Mrs. Gray has also attended the required workshops/professional development activities offered here on campus. &nbsp;She continually seeks out professional readings and research which she often shares with the faculty at faculty meetings.&nbsp;', 'Mrs. Gray have an excellent student evaluation on the survey items. &nbsp;Comments were positive with a couple of statements she is addressing in the classroom. &nbsp;Mrs. Gray accepts the comments from the students in a positive manner. &nbsp;She is eager to use those to improve her performance as a didactic instructor.&nbsp;<p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'Laura Gray', 'Wanda H. Capps ');
