rtify my CCNA R/S this summer and have been spending several hours each week in preparation.<span style="mso-spacerun:yes">&nbsp; </span>The NET 225 and NET 226 I taught this fall, has been helpful in my study efforts</span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:" times="" new="" roman",serif"=""><span style="text-decoration:none">&nbsp;</span></u></p>', 'Al will complete the necessary hours of professional development.', 'Mr. Spraker is a wonderful instructor and resource for our IT students. &nbsp;His experience and expertise, along with a great teaching style, ensure our students are well prepared and ready for the job market when they complete their degrees.', 'Al Spraker', 'W. Darell Matthews');
INSERT INTO `perfobj2` (`ID`, `employee`, `date_submitted`, `obj_setting_period`, `supervisor`, `section_1_employee`, `section_1_supervisor`, `section_2_employee`, `section_2_supervisor`, `evaluation_summary`, `employee_signature`, `supervisor_signature`) VALUES
(31, 'Loreta M. Jones', '2016-01-27', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<ol><li>Advised the NSO and registration for Fall 15and Spring 16 Semester</li><li>Utilized the NSO and SCC Tours to recruit for new students for the cosmetology department as follows: Sampson Co. Schools, "Jump Start Students; AVID TOUR, Union Middle School 6th grader; Sampson - Clinton YIC Career Fair Tour; TarHeel Challenge Tour; and College Gear Up Day.</li><li>Took the students on a field trip to Charlotte NC at the Fashion Focus Hair Show on October 4th and 5th, 2015 to explore new innovated skills and techniques for perms, hair color and hair cutting performances.</li><li>Advanced the students education in Small Business Classes in the Fall Semester (See classes below) especially "How to market your Customer using Customer Service."</li></ol>', 'Mrs. Jones has worked diligently to keep her department at the top. &nbsp;She is helping to implement new strategies that will ensure less disciplinary distractions in COS.', '<ol><li>Utilizing the skills we learn in our Customer Service (1 hr.) class in Fall Semester by Steve Carver addressing our clients and students by greeting them by name, warm smiles and assisting them to the salon floor, bus, and car.</li><li>Attended the Faculty and Staff/ Divisional meeting with Darell Matthews for the Fall (August 10th) and Spring (January 4th) Semester for about hour; Crisis Management Meeting on October 27th (1hour).</li><li>Attended the NCCCCIA Fall Conference Meeting on October 26th from 8am - 3pm at Central Peidmont Community College for updates with NC State Board of Cosmetic Arts Examiners and received 6 CEUS to help assist with the Cosmetology and Cosmetology Instructors License.</li><li>Attended the Fashion Focus Hair Show on October 4th and 5th in Charlotte NC and attended the following 8 CEU CLASSES for (1 hour each) credit: ARDELL: Want to Become a Lash Expert ??!!; GELISH Design Studio; MALIBU C: Top Tips for Color and Color Correction Plus; TIGI TIGI: Academy Collection - Real Hair for Real People; DEVA CURL:Curl Q; GIGI:Beautiful Smooth Skin the GiGi Way; JOHNNY B.: Elite Clipper Cutting; and DONALD SCOTT: Razor Cutting with Scissors at the Same Time.</li><li>Attended the following Small Business class at SCC to help advance our knowledge in business and customer service: Sept. 16th,(1-3pm) "Cosmetology and Business"; Oct. 14th. (1-3pm) "How to Market Your Customers", and Oct. 21st. (1-3pm) " Always Be Connecting the Dots."</li></ol>', 'Mrs. Jones will have completed her required 15 hours of professional development by the due date.', 'Overall Mrs. Jones is a wonderful educator. &nbsp;We are in the process of updating her equipment and setting restrictions in place that will allow her and her faculty to limit the disciplinary distractions.', 'Loreta M. Jones', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(32, 'Pharris Shirley', '2016-01-27', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p>1. Advised and enrolled studentsfor Cosmetology</p><p>2. Help assist Mrs. Jones with NSO for students who may be considering a career in Cosmetology.</p><p>3. Help coordinate a field trip to Charlotte, for the Fashion Focus Hair Show, October 4th and 5th.</p>', 'Mrs. Shirley has been an adjunct instructor for long enough to handle the rigors of a full-time faculty member. &nbsp;She is progressing as expected.', '<p>1. Implemented customer service training. Try to speak to and help anyone on campus. Show students the correct way to greet clients and interact.</p><p>2. Keeping up to date with the latest trends and techniques byattending the Fashion Focus hair show in Charlotte. Attended several CEU classes to include: Deva Curl, Johnny B Clipper Cutting, Malibu C: Tips for Corrective Color, TIGI Academy Real Hair for Real People, Donald Scott Razor Cutting and Gigi Beautiful Skin.</p><p>3. Small Business Classes on: Cosmetology and Business and How to Market Your Customers.</p><p>4. Attended my first NCCCCIA Fall Conference. </p><p>5. Crisis Management Meeting </p>', 'Mrs. Shirley will complete the required hours.', 'We are very pleased with having Mrs. Shirley as a full time faculty member.', 'Pharris Shirley', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(33, 'Jennifer Wiley', '2016-01-28', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoNormal">Successfully completed General Instructor School atFayetteville Technical Community College <o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Successfully completed the BLET School Directors ConferenceSeptember 2015<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Successfully completed the Leadership Summit and Workshop atNorth Carolina State University November 20, 2015<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Reviewed and applied requirements to manage the BLET program inorder to facilitate academies from September 2015 forward as Director of BasicLaw Enforcement Training<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Maintained oversight of the criminal justice academicdepartment as Criminal Justice Chair and successfully facilitated 21 credithoursFall 2015<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Attended community functions (as available) to promote SCC andgrow enrollment in Criminal Justice and BLET throughout the academic year (Job Fair at SCC and one is scheduled at University of Mount Olive for March 17, 2016)<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Facilitate and plan for the Academic Advisory Board Meeting for CriminalJustice for the 2015-2016 academic year<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">Continued to maintain working relationship with the local criminaljustice agencies in order to gain information about the recent procedures andtechnology in the field to be incorporated into the classroom. <o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">                 Successfully facilitated the first annual Criminal Justice and Basic Law Enforcement Training Job and Career Fair- November 2015</span><p><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><span style="font-size: 16px;">               Continued the relationship with the local paper- articles about BLET published on 8/25/15 and 9/30/15, article about the first job and career fair published in 10/2015</span></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><span style="font-size: 16px;">               Created and now maintained professional relationships with other community colleges (BLET programs) to share and implement new ideas (Website and recruiting)                           (FTCC BLET Director, Johnston CC BLET Director and <b style="font-size: 16px;">briefly</b></span></font><span style="font-size: 16px;">met with Sprunt Director)</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">               </span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">               Served/serving as Vice President to the Faculty Senate</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">               Served on the Retention study committee (Fall 2015)</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">               Attended meetings and assisted to plan for new program under Criminal Justice Technology and later oversee it (Emergency Management with fire and cjc tracks)</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">                  </span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">               Continue to plan for the second career and job fair for CJC/BLET to take place Spring 2016.</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">               Continue recruiting efforts in Spring 2016 for BLET entry Fall 2015</span></p><p><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></font></p><p><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></font><p><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA"></span></p></p>', 'Mrs. Wiley has helped to grow the CJC department and has proved to be an excellent BLET director.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="padding-left: 133.656px; padding-right: 133.656px;">Successfully completed General Instructor School at Fayetteville Technical Community College<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="padding-left: 133.656px; padding-right: 133.656px;"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="padding-left: 133.656px; padding-right: 133.656px;">Successfully completed the BLET School Directors Conference September 2015<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="padding-left: 133.656px; padding-right: 133.656px;"><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="padding-left: 133.656px; padding-right: 133.656px;">Successfully completed the Leadership Summit and Workshop at North Carolina State University November 20, 2015</p>', 'Mrs. Wiley will complete the required hours.', 'Mrs. Wiley has years of knowledge and experience that lend well to her incredible teaching style for CJC courses. &nbsp;She also has heavily marketed our BLET program to ensure we have academies, at least one, every semester. &nbsp;She is instrumental in the survival and growth of both CJC and BLET.', 'Jennifer Wiley', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(34, 'Barney Grady', '2016-01-28', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '-Working with Moodle and researching alternative delivery methods (Web, hybrid, web cam, etc...) for certain classes, that may increase enrollment by accommodating students that are unable to attend traditional students.<p><br></p><p>-Development of SST 140 is well underway. I am currently offering the course for the first time this semester and enrollment is at 26.</p>', 'Mr. Grady is progressing towards his goals.', '-Planned to attend a Green Building conference last fall and a schedule conflict, currently looking at another that I may attend this Spring. <p><br></p><p>-Planning to take the Moodle Course during its next offering.</p><p><br></p>', 'Mr. Grady will complete the required hours.', 'Mr. Grady, being a single-person department, has grown the BCT program and helped to ensure our checklists and materials are utilizing the latest information from NCCCS and the building construction community.', 'Barney D. Grady', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(35, 'Benita Hayes', '2016-01-28', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'Within the department, I have supervised and evaluated all full-time employees and adjunct faculty. Attended the College Fair Day and provided information about the department. I have completed scheduling and advised new and returning students each semester. Course syllabi are being updated each semester as I continue to teach the required course load.', 'Ms. Hayes has met or is progressing towards all of her goals.', 'Enrolled in and completed BIO 168 Anatomy and Physiology course to prepare for Medical Coding and Billing certification. Attended the Customer Service workshop for professional development in August.', 'Ms. Hayes will complete the required hours.', 'Ms. Hayes, along with her faculty, have kept the OA and MOA programs steady with students, and has been willing to assist with the instruction of CIS110.', 'Benita Faye Hayes', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(36, 'Reuben Cashwell', '2016-01-28', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '-Increased course content on AGR 226, AGR 150, ISC 112, and WLD 112.<p><br></p><p>-Will attend meetings with local industries to hear their needs.</p><p><br></p><p>-Promote the College to be the College of choice for the surrounding areas.</p>', 'Mr. Cashwell is making progress towards his performance objectives.', '-50% Completed on OSHA 10 HR text and updates', 'Mr. Cashwell should complete the required hours.', 'Mr. Cashwell is a valuable instructor in that he can teach in the IST program, the ANS program, and the WLD program. &nbsp;His years of experience are certainly an asset to our departments.', 'Reuben Cashwell', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(37, 'Edith Rogers', '2016-01-28', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '1. I have learned basic operations of the copier by studying the online users manual, along with trial and error. I will continue this objective to learn more features. Additionally,   I am learning to perform periodic routine in-house maintenance as recommended in the users manual.<p><br></p><p>2. I continue to study the Reference Guide that accompanies the new phone system. I have learned the basic features but wish to learn more of the advanced features.</p><p><br></p><p>3. Update of the student advisee files/program checklists is ongoing. I am currently assisting program chairs with evaluating transcripts for prospective graduates.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'Ms. Rogers is an absolutely vital entity to our division. &nbsp;Serving as Division Secretary, she is always willing to go above and beyond to help anyone.', '1. Membership in the NCAEOP (State educational office professionals organization) is current.<p><br></p><p>2. I did not attend the NCAEOP District 13 Annual meeting held in October; no seminars/workshops of interest were scheduled. Attendance at the annual State conference      is unlikely; I have noticed some changes in the program format and a change in the conference location.</p><p><br></p><p>3. I have not enrolled in a CE course so far but still would like to do so as time permits.</p><p><br></p><p>4. I continue to seek professional development opportunities, including activities related to customer service because the College is focusing on this as a mechanism to aid in    student retention.</p>', 'Ms. Rogers will complete the required hours.', 'There is absolutely no way our division would function as organized and as smoothly as it does without Ms. Rogers. &nbsp;She is always willing to assist anyone, student or staff, with anything they need. &nbsp;', 'Edith A. Rogers', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(38, 'Durwood M. King', '2016-01-29', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'Developed and administered PLC II & Electrical III courses in the Industrial Maintenance Mechanics Program of Study.<p>Expanded hands-on labs for ELC-117 Motors and Controls, and ELC-128 Intro to PLCs.<br></p><p>Assisted in preparation of grant request and selecting components for new Automation assembly line.<br></p><p>Networked with business/industry to stay informed of new technology to enhance workforce training.<br></p><p><br></p><p></p>', 'Durwood teaches both ConEd and Curriculum courses in several areas. &nbsp;His knowledge, experience, and expertise in those areas make him a valuable resource for the ITS program and for SCC.', '<p>Plans to attend an 8 hour Continuing Education course on National Electric Code for licensure renewal.<br></p><p>Plans to attend 2 day training course on the new SMC Automation assembly line when it arrives.</p>', 'Durwood will complete his required 15 hours of professional development', 'Durwood King is a valuable resource for SCC, the ITS programs, and ConEd. &nbsp;His knowledge and experience lends itself well to a variety of instructional areas. &nbsp;We are lucky to have him on faculty. &nbsp;WDM', 'Durwood M. King', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(39, 'Dana Meredith', '2016-02-01', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<ol><li>During spring registration assisted students in registration using Web-Advisor, also advised students in course selection to achieve their career and academic goals.<br></li><li>Working to put into place a Plumbing Certificate that would be available for night students.</li><li>Working to put into place a HVAC Certificate that would be available for night students.</li><li>Ammonia Refrigeration Certificate has been developed and approved by the state. Looking for an instructor to teach the program.</li></ol><p><br></p>', 'Serving as Dept. Chair, Mr. Meredith has grown his department by nearly 400% to one that is sought after by students and whose students are easily employed.', '<ol><li>Enrolled in SPA 120, Spanish for the Workplace for professional development hours.</li><li>Will schedule Advisory Committee meeting for spring.</li><li>Have visited Sager Creek, Smithfield, and Precision Machine in the Fall semester and representatives from these industries have visited our shop to view our program.</li><li>Working with Durwood King and Rueben Cashwell reviewing the possibility of adapting Mechtronics into our program. Will also be part of the advisory agenda to have input from our committee members.</li></ol>', 'Mr. Meredith will complete the required hours.', 'Mr. Meredith has been instrumental in growing his department by leaps and bounds. &nbsp;Local employers visit Mr. Merediths shop area frequently and are impressed with his graduates.', 'Dana Neil Meredith, Sr.', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(40, 'Michele Moore', '2016-02-01', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'More SCC students from different majors are inquiring about obtaining their certificate in Spanish Interpreting.<p><br></p><p>Having Emily Philips teaching all of the SPI classes has really been helpful for me and the students. She has been able to provide consistency, quality first-hand interpreting knowledge, and has been able to afford us the means to offer the Interpreting classes more often. I believe our students are completing degrees and certificates at a quicker pace.</p><p><br></p><p>I would like to advertise to other schools our online certificates. I know that there are other students in the system that could benefit from the Interpreting Certificate.</p>', 'Mrs. Moore has grown the SPI program immensely and has been able to recruit qualified adjuncts.', 'I am currently taking my last class for my SCC Web Design Certificate, DBA110. I plan on taking my Access 2013 Certification once this class is finished.<p><br></p><p>One of my students asked me if I ever used the Duolingo App and if I thought it would be beneficial for learning Spanish. I downloaded the app and Im currently learning French and Portuguese. A good app, and I think it will help my students with consistency and recognition of basic words.</p><p><br></p><p>I have taken a few webinars, focusing on Moodle. I love technology and I think learning more about Moodle, Respondus, and other items are important.</p>', 'Mrs. Moore will complete her required hours.', 'Mrs. Moore has done a wonderful job at growing the SPI program, recruiting students, and teaching SPA classes....all while being a single-person department.', 'Michele L. Moore', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(41, 'Lynn Cavenaugh', '2016-02-10', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'I believe that I have done a good job at keeping the department organized and updated. I continue to assist Faculty with their needs. Documentation is very important so I have been proofing all documents carefully prior to submitting them for approval in a timely manner. It is that time of year for graduates and I have been availalbe to notorize their documents as requested.&nbsp;', '', 'I have attended all workshops and training provided by Sampson Community College. I am looking forward to branching out and learning new activities and tasks.&nbsp;', '', '', 'Lynn Cavenaugh', ''),
(42, 'Robin Bradshaw', '2015-12-31', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1.The curriculum changes were implemented but some adjustments will be needed.<p><span style="font-size: 16px;">2.I continue to collect and analyze testing data which in turn causes the focus to shift to some of the weak area.</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">3. Student records continue to be maintained according to the Division of Health service Regulations guidelines.</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">4. The nursing lab is continued monitor to keep things in working order and adequately supplied.</span></p>', 'This evaluation is for the 2015-2016 academic year. Mrs. &nbsp;Bradshaw is meeting the objectives as stated. &nbsp;She continues to serve as coordinator for the NA and Phlebotomy programs and works with Richard Stephenson in making sure rules and regulations are maintained as required by the governing organizations and bodies.&nbsp;', 'I attended the Regional Training Session which &nbsp;is listed on my performance log. These sessions are very informative.<span style="font-size: 16px;">I have attended professional development workshops and self study class as well as online education.</span>', 'Engages in workshops on campus and those required for the NA program.&nbsp;', 'Dedicated employee. &nbsp;Her focus is primarily on students and their success. &nbsp;She is readily available to them, dedicated and motivated.&nbsp;', 'Robin Bradshaw', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(43, 'Vicky Williams', '2015-12-02', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman, serif;">I will continue to obtain knowledge of Medical Billing and Coding updates by&nbsp;attending the MOA System Conference and attending various online webinars.&nbsp; All&nbsp;syllabuses are updated to reflect change in new editions to the textbook in the Medical&nbsp;Billing and Coding.</span>', 'Mrs. Williams has been taking courses in MBC and is our prime instructor for those courses. &nbsp;DM', '<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman, serif;">I will continue to take training sessions to help gainknowledge of the courses that are being taught.I will continue to stay up to date on the new ICD-10 updates and passthese updates on to students to help prepare for the changes in new ICD-CM coding. Syllabus is prepared to cover aspects of new ICD-10-CMcoding.</span>', 'Mrs. Williams will complete the required hours. &nbsp;DM', 'Mrs. Williams has brought a wealth of experience in MOA to our programs. &nbsp;Together with Ms. Hayes they have increased the numbers in MOA. &nbsp;DM', 'Vicky Williams', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(44, 'Lisa Horne', '2016-12-02', '2016-2017', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<ul><li>I assist Mr. Chet Bass, Animal Science Department Chair, with requisitions, quizzes, etc.; whatever help he may need.</li><li>I continue to notarize various documents for faculty/staff and students.</li><li>I provide clerical assistance to the Occupational Faculty and any help they may need.</li><li>Continue to learn new features on the new phone system.</li></ul>', 'Lisa has been a huge help in getting Mr. Bass acclimated to the Dept. Chair role for the ANS program. &nbsp;She is also vital in maintaining communication and workflow with the Occupational Division faculty and staff. &nbsp;WDM', '<ul><li>Registration Meeting - August 8, 2016 (3 hrs.)</li><li>Division Meeting - November 9, 2016 (1 hr.)</li></ul>', 'Lisa will complete the required hours. &nbsp;WDM', 'Overall Lisa Horne has done a great job balancing two roles. &nbsp;As the Occupational Division secretary, I rely on her heavily for communication and paperwork flow for the division faculty and staff. &nbsp;WDM', 'Lisa Horne', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(45, 'Julia Amanda Bradshaw', '2016-12-14', '2016-2017', 'abutler@sampsoncc.edu', '- We have offered 29 of seminars to date thus far. As a reminder, the goal is to complete 66 seminars by June 30, 2017.<p>- The WomenWhoIspire Conference has been completed and was a huge success for not only the SBC but that of the college as a whole. Well received by the community.</p><p>- 3 new SBC featured videos were filmed in August-September and have since been published.</p><p>- A Small Business Saturday campaign was completed in partnership several community organizations. As a committee, we chose to offer a Passport Program due to measurable incomes. As a result, $2760 were documented through the program as being spent during that day in Sampson County.</p><p>- B2B is continuing as usual with continued success.</p><p>- The relationship with the NC Military Business Center has been placed on hold due to sickness of the liaison from the organization. We will revisit her health in January of 2017.</p><p>- The Southeastern NC Farm School has been planned and dates set. The program will begin on January 24th and be taught using the REAL Agribusiness Curriculum. The series will be taught in conjunction with JSCC at the Incubator kitchen in Duplin as a central location site.</p><p><br></p>', 'Your creativity, energy and knowledge have transformed SCCs Small Business Center into an exciting, invaluable resource for aspiring entrepreneurs and for business professionals throughout Sampson County. &nbsp;A week does not pass that someone doesnt comment to me about the wildly successful Women Who Inspire Conference saying it was by far THE BEST womens event ever held in Sampson County, and I agree. &nbsp;<p><br></p><p>You have brought new life into a program that was becoming a dinosaur and I applaud all that you have accomplished thus far this year.<br><p><br></p></p>', '- Attended the Annual Joint PD Conference in Asheville during the 3rd week of November. Served as Chair SBCN representative for the group. Great conference and networking time with others from across the state.<p>- Was unable to attend the Community College Annual Conference due to Hurricane Matthew. I have hopes of attending next year.<br></p><p>- Attended the NC Rural Assembly in Raleigh in late September. The focus was towards the medical field and how we can better meet their needs as a community college system with concern specifically towards workforce development.</p><p>- Attended SACS Conference in Atlanta as a team member from SCC. Great point of learning and networking with others from across the US.<br><p><br></p></p>', 'Excellent', 'As my days at SCC draw to a close, I am so excited to leave Continuing Education in the hands of an incredible woman who will lead the division into becoming a model program for SCC and the envy of Continuing Education divisions throughout North Carolinas community college system. &nbsp;You have a unique set of talents that will inspire and empower staff to work hard to achieve new goals, that will infuse the division with fresh ideas and cutting-edge technology, and that will forge strong partnerships internally and externally. &nbsp;I look forward to stepping back to marvel at the incredible things you will accomplish in this challenging, fulfilling new role.<p><br></p><p>I am so proud of you... of the person that you are and all that you have accomplished thus far. Count on my support as Im needed (doubtful!) as you take the helm. &nbsp;God bless and guide you.</p>', 'Julia Bradshaw', 'Ann B. Butler'),
(46, 'Rebecca Scott', '2017-01-03', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Goal 1 Objective 1 A variety of teaching styles were implemented to allow students learning opportunities through class activities and lab experiences.<p><br></p><p>2. Goal 1 Objective 4 Student records were maintained per guidelines of Division of Health Services Regulations.</p><p><br></p><p>3. Goal 5 Nurse Aide I curriculum was implemented to help prepare students to enter workforce.</p>', 'Agree with instructors comments. &nbsp;No problems identified at this point. &nbsp;Fall 2016 student evaluations were excellent with positive comments related to her instruction and interactions with students.&nbsp;', 'Attended Community College Conference in October to become knowledgeable in assisting students to have a successful experience in their career pathway. Attended workshop offered be Division of Health Services Regulations to remain updated on changes in Nurse Aide I program. Read e-mails from regional consultant regarding changes in Nurse Aide I program.', 'Agree with comments.&nbsp;', 'Mrs. Scott is certainly dedicated to her job. &nbsp;She rarely misses a day of instruction.', 'Rebecca Scott', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(47, 'Daphene C.  Lane', '2017-01-12', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<p><br></p><p>Objective related to SCC Goal 1 obj.1.5: Provide clinical simulation clinical experiences for freshman,practical nursing and senior students using SCCs high and low fidelity simulation equipment. Objective has been partially met. Simulation clinical experiences were provided for both the freshman and practical nursing students during the Fall 2016 semester. The freshman and practical nursing students will also be provided clinical simulation experiences this semester (Spring 2017). Senior nursing students will be provided this experience 2017.</p><p>Objective related to SCC Goal 3, obj.3: Enlist students to engage in a community service opportunity by participating in the SCC Annual. Phonathon.t. Students generated a sign up sheet to participate in the SCC Annual Phonathon. </p><p>Objective related to SCC Goal 4 Obj. 4: Provide remediation/retention activities such as test review and clarification sessions for students after class. Objective met. for the Fall semester, 100% of the students participated in the newly adopted retention plan. The students performed better on their units tests during Fall 2016 than they did Fall 2015. The unit test average for Fall Semester 2016 was 85.36 which was higher than the 82.09 for Fall 2015.</p><p>Objective related to SCC Goal 1 obj. 1.5: Implement concept-based strategies for students. Activities related to objective are progressing well. Faculty revised clinical paper work to reflect concept-based curriculum. Students were able to successfully complete the required paperwork Fall semester.</p>', 'Agree with Mrs. Laness comments. &nbsp;Her performance as a clinical stimulation instructor is above average and she is dedicated to making it realistic and challenging for the students to promote learning as a clinical experience. &nbsp;Mrs. Lanes Fall 2016 student evaluations were excellent with positive comments.&nbsp;', 'The Annual You Bought the Mannkin Now What? Simulation Conference is not being held due to the Simulation Conference in Orlando. Faculty will incorporate some other Professional Development and Personal Training activity.<p><br></p><p>NCCPNE Fall Conference was held just weeks after the Systems Conference and during the time of Flooded areas therefore we did not attend.</p><p><br></p><p>I am still in the process of working on the ATI Champion Modules.</p>', 'Mrs. Lane has enrolled in a course related to simulation in order to prepare for certification as a Simulation Instructor. &nbsp;She stays up to date on simulations through various workshops and information from the simulation companies.&nbsp;', 'Mrs. Lane is an instructor who is dedicated to student success not only in the classroom and their chosen profession but also to them personally. &nbsp;Her door is always opened to students for whatever reason.&nbsp;', 'Daphene C. Lane', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(48, 'Lisa Smith', '2017-01-12', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:" times="" new="" roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"times="" roman";mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:en-us;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa"="">I continue to advise and counsel students and provide effective teaching in an effort to enhance student retention and improve student goal completion and graduation rates.&nbsp;&nbsp; Data collection for ACEN accreditation is ongoing.&nbsp; The first-year ADN faculty have implemented retention strategies, including extra ATI assignments, BoardVitals question assignments, and individual test analysis and review/counselling for the first Unit Test of the semester.&nbsp; Retention of our NUR 111 students increased from 58% with the previous class to 70.5% with the current class.&nbsp; Similar efforts are being continued with the Spring courses.&nbsp;</span>', 'Agree with Dr. Smiths comments. &nbsp;Not only has retention increased but the performance level of the students didactically has increased. &nbsp;Dr. Smith is dedicated to meeting the goals she sets not only for herself but for the students as well.&nbsp;<p><br></p><p>Dr. Smiths Fall 2016 class and clinical student evaluations were excellent with positive comments related to her instruction.&nbsp;</p>', '<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: " times="" new="" roman",="" serif;"="">I participated in the campus workshop on August8, 2016.&nbsp; I continue to participate in departmentcommittee and faculty meetings as assigned.&nbsp;I attended the annual NCNA Convention on September 28-30, 2016 and earned 14 CEUs.&nbsp; I also attended the NCCCS Conference on October 9-11, 2016.&nbsp;In an effort to enhance my Nurse Educator experience and utilize my DNPdegree, I currently teach an online DNP course on a part-time basis in the university setting.&nbsp;</span>', 'Agree with Dr. Smiths comments. &nbsp;She continues to participate in professional development for personal enhancement as well as increases her knowledge related to instruction.&nbsp;', 'Dr. Smith is one who is organized, dedicated, motivated and a detailed individuals. &nbsp;She is never late in submitting assignments and they are always complete and concise. &nbsp;She is a team player and SCC is fortunate to have her on the team!. &nbsp;', 'Dr. Lisa S. Smith', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(49, 'Regina Parker', '2017-01-12', '2017-2018', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'Performance Objectives #1 from 08/12/2016 did not save correctly in this system. They were:<p>1. To promote academic excellence through quality instruction (Goal 1 Objective 1.1)</p><p>2. Increase retention through quality instruction, advising, and counseling (Goal 1 Objective 1.1)</p><p>3. Collect and compile data to monitor and improve student learning outcomes (Goal 1 Objective 1.5)</p><p>4. Collect data and compile reports to maintain ACEN accreditation (Goal 4)</p><p><br></p><p>Progress Conference #2:</p><p>I feel I am continuing to meet these objectives. NUR 111 has already shown an increase in retention in 2016 when compared to previous years. I have been involved with extensive one-on-one counseling with students after class to improve retention and student learning outcomes. And I continue to work on ACEN subcommittees where data is compiled and reported to maintain ACEN accreditation.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'I continue to be enrolled full-time in ECUs DNP/FNP program with planned graduation date May 2019. I renewed BLS, PALS, and ACLS in July 2016. I plan to attend the NC Nurse Practitioners Symposium in March 2017.', '', '', 'Regina Parker', ''),
(50, 'Regina Parker', '2017-01-12', '2017-2018', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'Performance Objectives #1 from 08/12/2016 did not save correctly in this system. They were:<p>1. To promote academic excellence through quality instruction (Goal 1 Objective 1.1)</p><p>2. Increase retention through quality instruction, advising, and counseling (Goal 1 Objective 1.1)</p><p>3. Collect and compile data to monitor and improve student learning outcomes (Goal 1 Objective 1.5)</p><p>4. Collect data and compile reports to maintain ACEN accreditation (Goal 4)</p><p><br></p><p>Progress Conference #2:</p><p>I feel I am continuing to meet these objectives. NUR 111 has already shown an increase in retention in 2016 when compared to previous years. I have been involved with extensive one-on-one counseling with students after class to improve retention and student learning outcomes. And I continue to work on ACEN subcommittees where data is compiled and reported to maintain ACEN accreditation.</p>', 'Agree with comments. &nbsp;Implementation of a new retention plan by the instructors as well as the commitment of the faculty has resulted in an increase in retention but also performance academically. &nbsp;', 'I continue to be enrolled full-time in ECUs DNP/FNP program with planned graduation date May 2019. I renewed BLS, PALS, and ACLS in July 2016. I plan to attend the NC Nurse Practitioners Symposium in March 2017.', 'Agree with comments.&nbsp;', 'Fall 2016 students evaluations were positive and comments supported the survey ranking. &nbsp;Comments supported Mrs. Parkers commitment in being a caring and compassionate facilitator for student learning.&nbsp;', 'Regina Parker', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(51, 'Kristina Edwards', '2017-01-17', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'Goal 1; Objective 1.1 -- Goal partially met. I encouraged all practical nursing students to participate in a test taking workshop, performed test reviews with students in the group and individual setting, made myself available during office hours and beyond. I am continuing these efforts in the second and third semesters of the program to improve completion and graduation rates.<p><br></p><p>Goal 1; Objective 1.4 -- Goal met. I have increased my availability to students, as stated previously. I do my best to maintain a positive attitude and an education conducive environment when interacting with students. Students have been educated on test taking skills and strategies.</p><p><br></p><p>Goal 4; Objective 4.3 -- Goal met. Students have been encouraged to increase involvement and voice their opinions during faculty meetings. Students have been attending faculty meetings regularly. </p>', 'Agree with instructors self-evaluation. &nbsp;Mrs. Edwards is always available to students and willing to be flexible in her schedule to accommodate their schedules. &nbsp;Student evaluations for clinical and didactic instruction for Fall 2016 were excellent with positive comments to support survey responses. &nbsp;', 'I have continued to stay current on best practices through continuing education opportunities available online. In addition, I have continued practicing my skills and reviewing policies in the clinical setting. I attended the North Carolina Community College System conference in October 2016 and attended several programs within the conference. I also completed my MOODLE certification course though Sampson Community College. I plan to attend a test-writing workshop as available.', 'Agree with self-evaluation.&nbsp;', 'It is evident through her interactions and dedication to the students that they truly do come first. &nbsp;She is always focused on making sure she provides them with the tools and resources to be successful.&nbsp;', 'Kristina C. Edwards', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(52, 'Alisha F. Carwise', '2017-02-15', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<p>Objective 1.1 - Objective in progress. I continuously inform students about campus and community activities to enhance learning as well as encourage participation. </p><p>Objective 1.4 - Objective met. Office hours are posted outside my door and students are encouraged to come by during office hours or make appointments. I also conduct individual and group test reviews to assist students in clarifying strengths and weaknesses. I have also provided my email address in order for students to communicate while off campus. </p><p>Objective 4.1 - Objective in progress. This objective is a continual process. I am currently serving on the curriculum committee of our SPEP committee which evaluates how the curriculum assists the students in meeting their learning outcomes.</p>', 'Mrs. Carwise is meeting her objectives as stated. &nbsp;Her student evaluations are excellent with positive comments related to didactic and clinical instruction.&nbsp;', 'The professional development objectives set were all met. I have successfully completed my Fall 2016 graduate courses and am currently enrolled for the Spring semester. I am still an employee at Cape Fear Valley Hospital that treats patients in all of Cumberland county and surrounding areas. I have also completed the moodle certification course provided by the college whichbroadened my knowledge of distance technologies and modalities. I feelthat I can better navigate the technological tools provided by the college.', 'Agree with instructors comments. &nbsp;She is continuing to work on completing the academic requirements for her MSN graduate degree. &nbsp;Mrs. Carwise does maintain her skills through employment in the clinical setting and actively seeks out learning opportunities and workshops to benefit the students and her performance as an instructor.&nbsp;', 'Excellent motivated and dedication instructor not only to her students but to the college as well.&nbsp;', 'Alisha F. Carwise, RN', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(53, 'Edith Rogers', '2017-01-27', '2016-2017', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '1. I have assisted our new instructor with various tasks that include preparing office door schedules, completing purchase requisitions, textbook adoption/desk copy &nbsp; &nbsp;request procedures, etc. I continue to assist as needed with questions concerning college policy and procedures.<p><br></p><p>2. I assist faculty advisers with preparation and upkeep of student advisee files by filing pertinent documents and forms and ensuring program checklists are updated to aid in more effective advisement and to help the students keep abreast of progress in their respective program(s). This objective is incomplete but ongoing.</p><p><br></p><p>3. I am learning to troubleshoot some problems that arise with the copier and solve them accordingly by following on-screen guidance instructions or by referring to the users manual. I am learning to perform routine maintenance.</p><p><br></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '1. Membership in the NCAEOP is current.<p><br></p><p>2. I attended the NCAEOP District 13 Annual meeting and workshops in October 2016.</p><p><br></p><p>3. I had interest in attending two professional development activities that were scheduled in other districts; however, these were canceled because of inclement weather (Hurricane Matthew). The meetings/workshops were rescheduled but then canceled again. I will continue to seek other relevant professional development opportunities.</p>', '', '', 'Edith A. Rogers', ''),
(55, 'Sabrina Pope', '2017-03-08', '2017-2018', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Promote academic excellence through quality instruction (Goal 1, Objective 1.1)<p>2. Participate with development of opportunities to assess students to participate in service learning (Goal 3, Objective 3.1)</p><p>3. Collect data to maintain ACEN accreditation (Goal 4).</p><p>4. Identify and meet community needs to promote open access to the college</p>', 'Agree with self-evaluation of performance objectives. &nbsp;No problems identified.&nbsp;', 'I will continue to enhance my professional and personal development by attending and participating in learning activites such as workshops and seminars. I will continue to participate in campus, community and department committess as assigned. I addition I will continue as a full-time student in the DNP-FNP program at Bradely University, with a tentative graduation date of June 2020.', 'Agree with self-evaluation. &nbsp;Mrs. Pope continually exhibits a life-long learner.&nbsp;', 'Ms. Pope is a team player and eager to assist in whatever is needed for the department as a whole.&nbsp;<p><br></p><p>Motivated, dedication and caring! &nbsp;Her student evaluations are excellent with positive comments!&nbsp;</p>', 'Sabrina Pope, MSN, RN', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(56, 'Laura O Gray', '2017-03-09', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1-Obj 8.2 - I am currently continuing to implement the clinicial site development grant (in the first year of implementation). &nbsp;This clinicial site was utilized last semester with positive reviews from students. &nbsp;I am continuing to work on this clinical to improve it.<p><br><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">2--Obj 3.1 - I continue to be the clinical&nbsp;instructor for farm worker&nbsp;health and it will continue this semester. &nbsp;This helps expand cultural awareness for our students.</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">3-Obj-2.3 - I continue to implement the flipped classroom and add voice recorded information to the PowerPoint&nbsp;for the students to access.</span></p></p>', 'Agree with instructors comments. &nbsp;Mrs. Gray has been innovative with the Farm workers Clinical Site Grant as well as flexible and creative in making it a meaningful experience for students and the clients. &nbsp;', '1-I am continuing to work part time at SCHD as a CNM. &nbsp;This helps maintain my clinicial competence.<p><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">2-I presented an update on the clincial site development grant at the annual state AHEC conference in February.</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 16px;">3-I continue to try to implement the customer service tips learned in the workchop last year.</span></p>', 'Agree with instructors comments.&nbsp;', 'No problems identified at this time.&nbsp;', 'Laura O Gray', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(57, 'Ashley Register', '2017-03-10', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">Weekly review of SCC website to check for accuracy of information regarding HealthcareDivision.</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:" times="" new="" roman","serif";mso-fareast-font-family:"times="" roman""=""><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Implemented a new filing system for student records regarding academic information.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Reviewed student health records for accuracy.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Greeted each student with a positive attitude,offering assistance and directing them to the appropriate advisor.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 5.25pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Maintained re-accreditation requirements such as meeting minutes, evaluations, contracts, and other documents.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'Ms. Register has been given the name "Awesome Ashley." &nbsp;She is doing a phenomenal job in meeting her role and responsibilities. &nbsp;She has organized and revamped some of the procedures within the department which has resulted in better efficiency and a pleasant work environment for the faculty and students.', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">Attended training witheach division secretary across campus. Attended Moodle training, web attendancetraining, and Person Vue Webinar for the new upload process.</span><o:p></o:p></p>', 'Agree with comments.&nbsp;', 'We are thrilled with the job Ashley is doing for the faculty, staff, and students here in the Healthcare Division. &nbsp;She is eager, dedicated, motivated and timely in all her assignments.&nbsp;', 'Ashley Register', 'Wanda H. Capps ');
INSERT INTO `perfobj2` (`ID`, `employee`, `date_submitted`, `obj_setting_period`, `supervisor`, `section_1_employee`, `section_1_supervisor`, `section_2_employee`, `section_2_supervisor`, `evaluation_summary`, `employee_signature`, `supervisor_signature`) VALUES
(58, 'Robin Bradshaw', '2017-03-10', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'Continue to prepare for Nurse Aide Reapproval.<p><br><p>Review student records for accuracy, maintain lab compliance, and review teaching standards.</p></p><p><br></p><p>Continue to maintain data for passage rates.</p>', 'Agree with Mrs. Bradshaws comments and self -evaluation. &nbsp;Mrs. Bradshaw has also served as a mentor for the newly hired &nbsp;Medical Assisting instructor and has also provided support to the new Administrative Assistant as needed.&nbsp;', 'Attended Community College Conference, Pearson Vue Webinar, Hosted and Attended Nurse Aide Regional Meetings. Provided community service at the A-dap center County Complex.', 'Mrs. Bradshaw stays abreast by attending workshops and completing continuing education credit for renewing nursing license.&nbsp;<p><br></p><p>Student evaluations of didactic and clinical instruction are excellent with no noted areas of concern.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Robin Bradshaw', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(59, 'Veronica F. Stevens', '2017-03-10', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Data from the review of student outcomes is being used to develop and improve relevant learning opportunities. Indicators of student outcomes are obtained from formative and summative evaluation methods such as examinations, clinical performance assessments, standardized testing, NCLEX passage rates and end of course evaluations. Data is used to determine student needs, inform relevant classroom and clinical instruction, and to improve student outcomes. Local, state and national standards of instruction are referenced when developing learning opportunities.<p><p>2. Effective advising, counseling and teaching to continues. Specific retention strategies such as individualized test review have been instituted to address student attrition. The retention rate for NUR 211 was 97 %. Ninety percent of the students who entered NUR 211 were retained. Retention rates for NUR 114 and 212 were 100%. All students who entered NUR 221 were retained.</p><p><br><p>3. The LPN to ADN online option is in its second year of operation. A review of the last course offering has prompted revisions to ensure the delivery of a curriculum that is current, relevant and effective.<br></p></p><p>4. Data for national accreditation is continually collected and updated. Work continues on the curriculum standard (standard 4), and contributions are made to the Systematic Program Evaluation Plan for our nursing programs.</p></p>', 'Agree with comments. &nbsp;Continues to go beyond expectations for excellence in the program and with students.&nbsp;', 'I recently completed a Moodle certification course (February, 2017) to update knowledge obtained from the 2015 certification course. I plan to attend the Nurse Practitioner Symposium in March to enhance my skills and knowledge as an advanced practice nurse. I continue to engage in clinical practice.', 'Agree with Dr. Stevens comments. &nbsp;', 'Her student evaluations are excellent with positive comments. &nbsp;No area of concerns noted. Mrs. Stevens also developed NUR 211 into an online course to meet the need of a student. Dr. Stevens is always willing to go beyond the required responsibilities of her job.. &nbsp;She is always willing to step in no matter the area including programs outside of the nursing department.&nbsp;', 'Dr. Veronica F. Stevens', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(60, 'Misti Turnage', '2017-03-13', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'I feel like that my confidence with instruction has greatly improved. I have also learned how to better prioritize my daily task.<p><br></p><p>I have contacted local facilities to discuss the Medical Assisting program, preceptorships and I have also discussed the benefits of hiring Medical Assistants.</p>', 'Misti is adapting well with transitioning from the clinical arena to education. &nbsp;She has devoted a great deal of time to setting up the program and the settings for the Medical Assisting Program. &nbsp;She is willing to reach out for assistance when needed and is mentored by nursing and nurse aide faculty for her position.&nbsp;', 'Attended SCC "Welcome Back" seminar, Moodle training, Web attendance training, NCCCSC, visited JCC on several occasions regarding MA program.', 'Agree with comments.&nbsp;<p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'Mistis student evaluations are excellent with positive comments from the student and no noted areas of concern.&nbsp;', 'Misti Turnage, CMA, AAMA', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(61, 'Krystle Edge', '2017-03-21', '2016-2017', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. I fostered completion in our nursing program by offering quality advising to new and returning students.&nbsp;<p>2. I brought the innovative techniques of Kahoot quizzing and prezi interative concept maps to the other instructors and students for use.</p><p>3. I helped the students participate in service learning by taking them to senior centers and assisting with preparing meals for meals on wheels and through community education.</p><p>4. I collected data and organized it to maintain ACEN accreditation.&nbsp;</p>', 'Agree with faculty comments. &nbsp;Mrs. Edge has brought innovative techniques from workshops into the classroom and clinical setting. &nbsp;She has also shared with the students applications to assist in fostering student success. &nbsp;She has participated with the students in service learning. &nbsp;She continues to be active in acquiring information for ACEN accreditation.&nbsp;', 'I have continued my education for my masters degree of nursing education and plan to graduate on December 15, 2017 from ECU. I have participated in all assigned committees and conferences. I continue to maintain my membership in AWHONN and my Inpatient Obstetric certification.&nbsp;', 'Agree. &nbsp;Mrs. Edge will complete her MSN degree December of 2017!&nbsp;<p><br></p>', 'Krystle is adapting well from the clinical practitioner side of the nursing world to that of education. &nbsp;Student evaluations are excellent with positive comments. &nbsp;Several issues discussed related to improvement for future.', 'Krystle Edge', 'Wanda H. Capps ');
INSERT INTO `perfobj3` (`ID`, `employee`, `date_submitted`, `obj_setting_period`, `supervisor`, `section_1_employee`, `section_1_supervisor`, `section_2_employee`, `section_2_supervisor`, `evaluation_summary`, `employee_signature`, `supervisor_signature`) VALUES
(1, 'Darrell Manuel', '2016-04-25', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Obtained training on Moodle updates; Attended Respondus training for use during on-line exams.<p><p>2. Maintaining BLET class files for current class and updated F-16 files.<br></p><p>3. Counseled students during this semester and have been conducting preregistration for next semester.<br></p></p>', 'Mr. Manuel has met all goals.', '1. Attended the BLET 2 day conferrence for Directors and QAs.<p>2. Have attended Moodle training at SCC given by the Moodle SCC Staff.</p><p>3. Attended Active Shooter training at SCC.</p><p>4. Attended Emergency Response training at SCC.</p><p><br></p>', 'Mr. Manuel has met the required hours.', 'Mr. Manuel is a valuable asset to the CJC and BLET programs. &nbsp;With his years of experience and training, he has proven to be a fantastic instructor.', 'Darrell Manuel', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(2, 'Reuben Cashwell', '2016-04-26', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<ul><li>Completed lesson plans, home assignments, labs, and PowerPoints as needed for classes: AGR 150, ISC 112 & WLD 112</li><li>Attended and participation in recruitment activities, ie...Clinton High Career Fair, Advisory meetings, Ag Day, etc.</li><li>Participated in the foundation phonathon with VP of the Foundation from Hog Slat</li></ul>', 'Mr. Cashwell has met his goals.', '<ul><li>Completed 10 hours of OSHA online training to update knowledge of the current industrial safety initiatives</li><li>Studied online resources to better understand government programs involved with conservation incentives such as Ag Wrap Equipment, CSP and others to educate Ag students in Ag Economics 110; this completed 15 hours objectives</li></ul>', 'Mr. Cashwell has completed the required hours.', 'Mr. Cashwell is a unique asset in that he can teach in 3 separate departments. &nbsp;His years of experience and versatility make him a valuable employee.', 'Reuben Cashwell', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(3, 'Dana N. Meredith Sr', '2016-04-26', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '* Promoted and provided guidance to students in "A VOICE" QEP. Demonstration and guidance on the use of Web Advisor.<p>* Developed and presented Plumbing and HVAC certificate checksheets to Division Chair.</p><p>*Continuing to search for instructor to support Ammonia Refrigeration Certificate.</p><p>* Provided guidance and support on $250,000 grant from Progress Energy (Janna Bass, Katie Brown, & Durwood King)</p>', 'Mr. Meredith has met his goals and we have secured the grant funding from Progress Energy.', '* Obtained professional development hours taking SPA 120 Spanish in the workplace.<p>* Hosted industry to tour shop: Sager Creek, Smithfield Packing, Enviva Pellets Sampson, Georgia Pacific, Precision Machining.</p><p>* Explored the possibility of changing Industrial Systems Program to Mechatronics. Mechatronics provide students with a wider range of electrical courses. Working with R. Cashwell, Durwood King and presenting to Advisory Committee.</p>', 'Mr. Meredith has met his required hours.', 'Mr. Meredith has grown his program nearly 400% and is producing top-quality graduates sought after by local employers. &nbsp;On top of the curriculum students he is teaching, he and his faculty have a thriving Continuing Education group whose employers are absolutely thrilled with the training their employees are receiving through Mr. Meredith and his faculty.', 'Dana Neil Meredith, Sr.', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(4, 'Regina Burgin', '2016-05-25', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'I feel that I have made progress towards my personal performance objectives this academic year through quality instruction and assisting with advising students. I continue to collect data for SLOs, as well as ACEN standard reports, and actively assist students with registration needs.', 'Ms. Burgin does provide quality instruction. &nbsp;In spite of efforts, retention as &nbsp;has not increased and the department as a whole will be brainstorming on way to increase retention in those courses which have a low retention rate and will be implemented across all courses. &nbsp;Agree with Ms. Burgins comments.&nbsp;<p><br></p>', 'I stay current with acute care nursing trends by continuing to work part-time as a staff nurse in an acute care hospital. Ive completed more than the required continuing education credits this year for professional development, and I completed the Moodle Certification Course offered at SCC this academic year.', 'Agree with comments.', 'Ms. Burgin is dependable and rarely misses work and if so it is due to illness or family illness. &nbsp;Student evaluations were shared and discussed with areas of concern noted and strategies/suggestions discussed.&nbsp;', 'Regina Burgin', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(5, 'Lisa S. Smith', '2016-07-11', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoNormal">Fostering student goal completion through qualityinstruction, in an effort to improve graduation rates, is an ongoing priorityand overall goal. I have been successfulin advising and counseling students appropriately and continue to provideeffecting teaching, both in the classroom and clinical setting. Innovation is utilized and continuallyassessed by the nursing faculty.Implementation of my DNP project (utilizing concept maps to enhance criticalthinking development), occurred during fall semester 2015 and while notsuccessful in increasing Critical Thinking scores on the ATI ProctoredAssessment, areas of improvement were observed and will be utilized to enhancefuture nursing courses. I have collectedand compiled data on Student Learning Outcomes (SLOs) for NUR 111, 112, and113. Data collection for ACENaccreditation has been ongoing with reports presented at scheduled meetings andfiled appropriately in their respected files in the nursing department.<o:p></o:p></p>', 'Agree with Dr. Smiths comments..she does provide quality instruction, advising and counseling. &nbsp;The department will be brainstorming on ways to increase retention in those courses which have a low retention rate and will be implemented across all courses. &nbsp;Dr. Smith is ALWAYS punctual with data and reports as required and needed for the department and for me when needed. &nbsp;She satisfactorily meets her duties as a didactic and clinical instructor. &nbsp;', '<p class="MsoNormal">In addition to the comments provided on the #2 ProgressConference, I have continued as a full-time student at Gardner-Webb University (GWU)during the 2015-2016 year, obtaining my Doctor of Nursing Practice degree inMay 2016 while maintaining a 4.0 GPA throughout my studies. I have maintained my professional involvementwith Sigma Theta Tau International Honor Society of Nursing (STTI), with dualenrollment in the Phi Upsilon and Theta Iota Chapters of STTI. Additionally, I remain a professional memberof the American Nurses Association (ANA) and the NC Nurses Association (NCNA). I presented my DNP Capstone Project at GWU onApril 21, 2016. My capstone project dissertationhas been delivered by GWU to ProQuest for publication dissemination. Additionally, I have attended scheduled SCC FacultySenate and Nursing Faculty Department meetings.<o:p></o:p></p>', 'Agree with Dr. Smiths comments. &nbsp;Dr. Smith also worked at the foundation phone-a-thon and encouraged nursing students to do the same. always serving as a role model. &nbsp;', 'Dr. Smiths commitment to her job responsibilities and the students is exemplary. &nbsp;She is willing to help with whatever is asked of her. &nbsp;She is to be commended for her outstanding educational achievement!', 'Lisa S. Smith', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(6, 'Rebecca Scott', '2016-06-22', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span style="font-size:16px;undefined">1. &nbsp;A variety of teaching styles were implemented to promote student engagement and learning opportunities.</span><p>2. Student records were maintained per Division of Health Services Regulations guidelines.</p><p>3. Nurse Aide I curriculum was implemented per guidelines of Division of Health Services Regulations.</p>', 'Agree with Mrs. Scotts comments and she has met her performance objectives as stated. &nbsp;She provides students with an interactive classroom setting and activities. &nbsp;Her documentation of student records and other paperwork necessary for Division of Health Service Regulation is exemplary and complete. &nbsp;Mrs. Scott stays abreast of state mandated changes to ensure accurate quality instruction.&nbsp;', 'Read updates received via e-mail from regional consultant regarding changes in the Nurse Aide I program. Attended Nurse Aide I regional training offered by Division of Health Services Regulations regarding updates on Nurse Aide I training program.', 'Attends all meetings required by the Division of Health Service Regulations', 'Mrs. Scott has a strong work ethic and desire to do her best at all times. &nbsp;She is hard-working, dependable, punctual at all times, and commitment to her job. &nbsp;She is a true asset to the Nurse Aide program.&nbsp;', 'Rebecca Scott', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(7, 'W. Darell Matthews', '2016-06-28', '2015-2016', 'bstarling@sampsoncc.edu', '<ol><li>Help faculty adjust to the new Fall 2015 checklists for each program area.</li><ol><li>The new Fall 2015 checklists are in place and have been used for nearly 1 year. &nbsp;We have made a few other changes to other program checklists as well along the way.</li></ol><li>Successfully close out the Horticulture program in December 2015.</li><ol><li>Our last Horticulture student finished all of his HORT courses in December 2015.</li></ol><li>Assist Dept. Chairs with the inclusion of newer courses, certificates, and programs...as seen necessary by our students and community.</li><ol><li>We have successfully integrated new courses as both core, other major, and elective courses.</li></ol><li>Find an IT instructor who can complete Cisco AI certification and begin teaching new IT courses.</li><ol><li>Nathan McKee has come onboard as a full-time CIT instructor. &nbsp;He has successfully completed Security+ certification.</li></ol></ol>', '', '<ol><li>Complete the minimum 15 hours of required professional development.</li><ol><li>I have completed 15+ hours of online and face-to-face professional development.</li></ol><li>Complete the Udemy.com Web Development Course.</li><ol><li>I have completed the Udemy.com Web Development Course as professional development to teach CIS115 and WEB110.</li></ol></ol>', '', '', 'W. Darell Matthews', ''),
(8, 'Bruce Creech', '2016-06-28', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'Assuming the role of Dept. Chair has been interesting.<p>I enjoy the challenges of teaching and having more responsibility.</p><p>Hopefully, I can have a bit more time to increase the online aspect of the BA and ACC programs.</p><p>Ive done several voice-overs for the New Student Orientation Video and phone recordings.</p>', 'Bruce has done an outstanding job as dept. chair. &nbsp;DM', 'I am taking Spanish 111 to increase my language skills with my Hispanic students', 'Bruce has completed the required hours. &nbsp;DM', 'Overall Bruce has done a fantastic job as dept. chair for BA/ACCT. &nbsp;There were a couple rough areas that we have discussed. &nbsp;DM', 'Bruce Creech', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(9, 'Pharris Shirley', '2016-05-16', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p>1. Advised and enrolled student for Cosmetology for Summer and Fall Semesters </p><p>2. Assist Mrs. Jones with NSO for students who may considering a field in Cosmetology</p><p>3. Help coordinate a field trip to Charlotte, for the Fashion Focus Hair Show, October 4th and 5th </p><p>4. Career Day for prospective students May 3, 2016 from 6-8 pm.</p><p>5. Invited Business Professionals to speak with students on a professional level to inspire them to continue this field. Salons owners, Product Demonstrators, and Empowerment Professionals spoke with students.</p>', 'Mrs. Shirley has proven to be a great, full-time addition to the COS dept. DM', '<p>1. Implemented customer service training. Try to help anyone on campus. Show students the correct way to greet clients and interact.</p><p>2. Keeping up to date with the latest trends and techinuques by attending the Fashion Focus hair show in Charlotte. Attended several CEU classes to include: Deval Curl, Johnnny B Clipper Cutting, Malibu C: Tips for Corrective Color, TIGI Academy Real Hair for Real People, Donald Scott Razor Cutting and GIGI Beautiful Skin.</p><p>3. Small Business Classes on: Cosmetology and Business and How to Market Your Customers</p><p>4. Attended my first NCCCCIA Fall Conference </p><p>5. Crisis Management Meeting</p><p>6. Spring Conference at the NCCCCIA for updates on the NC State Board of Cosmetic Arts on April 4, 2016</p>', 'Mrs. Shirley has completed the required hours. DM', 'I am very pleased with Mrs. Shirleys performance. DM', 'Pharris Shirley', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(10, 'Laurie Hamilton', '2016-07-06', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Organize focus group: Focus group included males and females, graduating and fairly new students, and mixed races. Students were overall quite happy with departments ability to meet their needs. Two suggestions were made: The department needs two full-time instructors in order to offer enough classes at times to meet students needs to graduate on time. Student Services needs to learn more about the program in order to be able to better advise incoming students prior to meeting with department head.<p><br></p><p>2. Instead of adding voice instruction to ANS 110 course, ANS 141 was completely revamped by adding section tests, midterm and final exams on Moodle. New topics were included and powerpoints for some sections were developed. This should make the course better able to be taught both from a F2F classroom and a Web platform.</p><p>3. Even with IT assistance it was not possible to change the format of videos in ANS 140. Instead, video and written instructions were developed to assist students in adding the formats of the current videos to their browsers so they could watch them.</p>', 'Dr. Hamilton has performed well being a single-person department and taking care of all the courses and students. DM', 'Veterinary licensure requirements were met and license renewed.<p><br></p><p>Moodle training was completed.</p><p>USDA/APHI<i>S </i>were completed and national accreditation was renewed.</p>', 'Dr. Hamilton has completed the required hours. DM', 'Dr. Hamilton was given the role of Dept. Chair and has done a fantastic job. &nbsp;She, along with a couple adjuncts, have offered the required courses for her students as well as teaching courses via our Polycom for CFHS. &nbsp;Dr. Hamilton has done an excellent job in all aspects. &nbsp;DM', 'Prefer not to sign prior to actual meeting', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(11, 'Loreta M. Jones', '2016-07-07', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Advised through NSO for the Fall 2015 to Summer 2016 and for the Fall 2016 semester.<p>2. Utilized the NSO and SCC Tours to recruit for new students for the cosmetology program as the Department Chair to the following : Sampson County Schools, "Jump Start Students; avid tour, Union Middle School 6th graders; Sampson-Clinton YIC Career Fair Tour; TarHeel Challenge Tour; and College Gear Up Day.</p><p>3. Took the students on a field trip to Charlotte NC at the Fashion Focus Hair Show on October 4th and 5th, 2015 top explore new innovated skills and techniques for perms, hair color, and hair cutting performances.</p><p>4. Advanced the students education in Small Business Classes in the Fall Semester(See classes listed below), especially "How to market your Customer using Customer Service.</p><p>5. Enhanced our department in the reception area and manicure room with new and updated furniture. We have a new projector/ with screen in the beginners department. New Monitor/ cameras for the Cosmetology department with the assistants of Darell Matthews.</p>', 'Mrs. Jones has done a fantastic job as Dept. Chair and controlling the discipline issues in the COS dept. DM', '1. Utilizing the skills we learn in our Customer Service (1hr.) class, in the Fall Semester by Steve Carver, addressing our clients and students by greeting them by name, warm smiles and assisting them to the salon floor, bus, and car.<p>2.Attending the Faculty and Staff/Divisional meeting with Darell Matthews for the Fall(August 10th) and Spring (January 4th) Semester for about an hour;Crisis Management Meeting on October 27th (1 hour), and updating my staff after every dfivision meeting about 30mins.</p><p>3. Attended the NCCCCIA Fall Conference Meeting on October 26th from 8am-3pm at Central Peidmont CC for updates with NC State Board of Cosmetic Arts Examiners and received 6 CEUS to help assist with the Cosmetology and Cosmetology Instructors Licensure.</p><p>4.Attended the Fashion Focus Hair Show on October 4th and 5th in Charlotte NC and attended the following 8 CEU classes for (1) hour each for credit: ARDELL: Want to Become a Lash Expert??!!; GELISH Design Studio; MALIBU C: Top Tips FOR Color and Color Correction Plus; TIGI TIGI: Acadamy Collection - Real Hair for Real People; DEVA CURL: Curl Q; GIGI: Beautiful Smooth Skin the GIGI Way; JOHNNY B.: Elite Clipper Cutting; and DONALD SCOTT: Razor Cutting with Scissors at the Same Time.</p><p>5. Attended the following Small Business clas at SCC to help advance our knowledge in business and customer service: Sept. 16th, (1-3pm) "Cosmetology and Business"; Oct. 14th. (13pm) " How to Market Your Customers", and Oct. 21st. (1-3pm) "Always Be Connecting the Dots."</p><p>6. Attended the DL Roope Adminstration at Raleigh NC at Wake Tech CC for the updates on the new Cosmetology state exam from 10am-4pm.</p><p>7. Received an Associate in Biblical Studies from North Carolina Theological Seminary.</p>', 'Mrs. Jones has completed the required hours. &nbsp;DM', 'I am very pleased with Mrs. Jones work in our COS dept. &nbsp;She and her staff have managed to control disciplinary issues while offering 20 students a chance to get their hours and complete their degree. &nbsp;She has done a great job. &nbsp;DM', 'Loreta M. Jones', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(12, 'Laura O Gray', '2016-07-11', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1-Obj 1.4 - Met - I attended the freshman nursing student welcme luncheon, the senior nursing student graduation luncheon, and a senior dinner.<p>2-Obj 8.1 - Met - I applied for and received approval for an AHEC Clincial Site Develpment Grant.</p><p>3-Obj 1.1 - Met - I have participated in advising, counseling, and effective teaching this year.</p><p>4-Obj 4.1 and 4.3 - Met - I have collected data and helped to maintain documentation for ACEN accreditation. Also, we all participated in a focused site visit by ACEN this year.</p>', 'Agree with Mrs. Grays comments. &nbsp;Mrs. Gray took the initiative to complete an application grant in order to apply for a Clinical Site Development Grant. &nbsp;This Grant is receiving high praise for the uniqueness of it as well as the population this grant will serve while providing an opportunity for students to experience the culture of seasonal farm workers. &nbsp;', '1- Partially met - I did not complete the SCC moodle certification but did attend SimMan 3G training.<p>2- Met - I no longer work at SRMC but am working part time at Sampson County Health Department as a CNM to maintain clinicial competence and expertise.</p><p>3- Not met - I no longer am active with the Roseboro NC-STEP committee.</p>', 'Agree with comments. &nbsp;Mrs. Gray is encouraged to complete the moodle certification course when offered again.&nbsp;', 'Mrs. Gray is to be commended for her work on the grant. &nbsp;She is dependable and willing to do whatever is asked of her. &nbsp;Student evaluations were reviewed and discussed with emphasis placed on areas needing development/improvement as an instructor. &nbsp;Great team member!&nbsp;', 'Laura O Gray', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(13, 'Durwood M. King', '0007-11-16', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p>Networked with Butterball LLC in choosing specific Allen Bradley Variable Frequency Drives (VFDs) common to their plant, to provide training to match their needs. </p><p><br></p><p>Added new Butterball class: "Electrical III" which includes wiring and troubleshooting of more advanced Motor Control circuits.Also added Variable Frequency Drives wiring, programming and troubleshooting</p><p><br></p><p>Expanded labs for ELC-117 Motors and Controls for wiring andtroubleshooting of more advanced Motor Control circuits.Also addedVariable Frequency Drives (VFDs) wiring, programming and troubleshooting. </p><p><br></p><p>Assisted inprocess of applying for Duke Energy grant for the newSMC Automation Equipment.</p>', 'Mr. King does an excellent job combining ConEd teaching with curriculum teaching, as well as developing new courses for our local industries. &nbsp;DM', '<p>Attended 8 hours Continuing Education class on the National Electric Code for license renewal (May 20, 2016)</p><p>Attended 16 hours training on the new SMC Automation Training Equipment,June 28-29, 2016)</p>', 'Mr. King has completed the required hours. DM', 'We are lucky to have Mr. King as an instructor for both curriculum and ConEd. &nbsp;DM', 'Durwood M. King', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(14, 'Alisha F. Carwise', '2016-07-12', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'During this academic year, I have provided multiple opportunities for students to engage while in class, clinical, posted office hours, scheduled appointments, Moodle technology as well as email.<p>During advisement, I have assessed the students access to technology and promoted access to distance learning class sections. </p><p>During this academic year, I have promoted student involvement in service learning projects in the community. I was also involved in coordinating a health fair on campus that was open to the community which provided reinforcement of teaching to the students and health education to the public.</p>', 'Agree with Mrs. Carwises comments. &nbsp;Her performance as a didactic instructor are improving as she transitions from the role of clinical instructor to the classroom setting. &nbsp;', 'I have maintained BLS and ACLS certifications.<p>I was unable to attend the test-item writing workshop due to funding.</p><p>I have maintain knowledge and currency in medical-surgical nursing through continued education credits as well as maintaining employment at a local acute care facility as a registered nurse.</p>', 'Agree. &nbsp;Mrs. Carwise is also currently enrolled in the MSN program at ECU. &nbsp;Her student evaluations have improved from the previous year. &nbsp;', 'Mrs. Carwise is a team player. &nbsp;She is approachable and professional in her interactions with students and fellow employees. &nbsp;Student evaluations shared and discussed. &nbsp;', 'Alisha F. Carwise, RN', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(15, 'Jennifer Wiley', '2016-07-12', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol"><span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><!--[endif]-->Added a new program for the community to theCriminal Justice Department: Submitted approval for new program for EmergencyManagement degree/certificate to begin Fall 2016 (searching for adjunct and selected texts)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol"><span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><!--[endif]-->Planned and held the Spring job and career fairfor Criminal Justice Technology, BLET and invited Fire and Technical Rescue andemergency services to work together from Continuing education for this eventheld on April 26, 2016 1-5 PM in the Warren Center (articles appeared in ourlocal newspaper on this event) (create the event on our facebook and updateagencies attending as they RSVP for students and the community)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol"><span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><!--[endif]-->Planned Coffee with a Cop for May 3 1130-1 pm tobuild relationship with local leo and students/community- gives students achance to learn about BLET (applied for/awarded grant $300)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--></p><span style="font-size:18px;font-family: Times New Roman; text-indent: -0.25in;"><span style="font-size:18px;font-family: Times New Roman; text-indent: -0.25in;"><span style="font-size:16px;font-family: Times New Roman; text-indent: -0.25in;"><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 16px;">* Completed additional duties and assisted with BLET Director position &nbsp;on the pre delivery, post delivery, and took the students to the state exam for BLET Academy September 2015 class- June 2016</span></p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; text-indent: -0.25in; font-size: 16px;">* Will continue with BLET Director position in addition to CJC /EM Chair for future Academies in 2016-2017</span></p></span><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"></p></span>', 'Somehow the text Jennifer added above came through as Greek, but she has done a fantastic job as CJC dept. chair and BLET Director. &nbsp;DM', 'Successfully completed General Instructor School at Fayetteville Technical Community College - maintained General Instructor Certification (renewed already)<p><p>Successfully completed BLET Directors Conference (9/2015)</p><p>Successfully completed the Leadership Summit and Workshop at North Carolina State University (November 2015)</p><p>Attended the BLET Regional Meeting (July 2016)</p><p>Completed New BLET Director Training sessions/orientation by Training and Standards with Brimm on 6/15/2016 (waiting on completion certificate from them at this time)</p><p><br></p><p><b>Additional Professional Development Hours Log emailed (25 hours)</b></p><p>Customer Service at the College (8/10/15 1 hour), Journal Article Review: Taking Student Retention Seriously- Rethinking the First year of College (8/12/15 1 hour), Online Webinar by Innovative Educators- 15 Strategies to re-invigorate your professional development program (8/19/2015 1 hour), Online Webinar by Innovative Educators- Dealing with Ethical Dilemmas- Strategies for leaders in higher education (8/19/2015 1 hour), Podcast/Webinar by Magna Publications - Checklist for launching an online degree program (9/2/15 30 minutes), North Carolina Traiing and Standards Conference - Bias Policing and Updates to BLET (9/9/15 and 9/10/15, 12 hours), Online Webinar- Inside Higher Ed- Data, Analytics, and Student Learning (9/29/15 1 hour), North Carolina State University Leadership Summit- Leadership that leads with a cross generational mindset (11/20/15 8 hours).</p><p><p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol"><span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: Times New Roman;">    </span></span><br></p></p></p>', 'Jennifer has completed the required hours. DM', 'I am very pleased with Mrs. Wileys performance both as CJC dept. chair and as BLET Director. &nbsp;CJC has lost a few students, but our BLET has increased. &nbsp;DM', 'Jennifer Wiley', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(16, 'Daphene C.  Lane', '2016-07-12', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', 'Time was allowed after each simulation for students concerns and comments regarding their performance. Students were allowed to discuss their strengths as well as their weaknesses after each simulation experience. Goal 1, obj. 1.4<p><br></p><p>Students participated in the SCC Annual Phonathon. They also signed up to Mary Gran Nursing Centers Relay for Life Pageant. However, the Pageant was canceled. Goal 3, obj. 3</p><p>Curriculum changes mandated by the Concept Based Curriculum were made and implemented for the 2015-2016 school year. Goal 4, obj. 4</p><p>Both freshman and practical nursing students rotated through the simulation lab during the Fall 2015 and Spring 2016 semesters. Goal 1, obj. 1.5</p>', 'Mrs. Lane is continuing to expand and provide additional clinical, lab as well as additional learning opportunities through simulation. &nbsp;She encourages students to participate in community service and attends the functions with them. &nbsp;Agree with Mrs. Lanes self evaluation.&nbsp;', 'Objective related to attending the North Carolina Council of Practical Nursing Educators. was not met. Instead I attended the Simulation Conference and the ADN Council meeting on incorporating concepts practices in our curriculum.<p><br></p><p>I did become a member of the NCNA Simulation Council, March 2016. Attended my first meeting at the conference.</p><p>I am in the process of preparing to complete the modules for becoming an ATI Champion for the associate degree and practical nursing programs.</p><p><p><br></p><p><br></p></p>', 'Mrs. Lane stays abreast of current literature and best practices related to curriculum, clinical and simulation instruction. &nbsp;Agree with self-evaluation.&nbsp;', 'No problems identified.&nbsp;', 'Daphene C. Lane', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(17, 'Krystle Edge', '2016-07-13', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<p>1. (Objective 1.3) Objective met.Knowledge on advising students in selecting an appropriate course schedule was increased evidenced by participating in new student registration with the help of a mentor.</p><p>2. (Objective 4.1) Objective met. Data collected for assessment of student learning outcomes each semester.</p><p>3. (Objective 4.1) Objective met. Data collected and organized to maintain ACEN accreditation by work on Standard 3 with team members.</p><p>4. (Objective 1.1) Objective met. Provided quality classroom instruction for one classroom hour and for clinical instruction. </p>', 'Mrs. Edge is continuing to gain knowledge related to advising and registering students. The department as a whole will be working on an additional retention plan to increase completion and retention rates. &nbsp;She is contributing to data collection for ACEN and is continuing to learn the process of accreditation and the Systematic Program Evaluation Plan.&nbsp;', 'I participated in two workshops; one on the concept based curriculum in April of 2016 and one on campus with Sim Man 3G in June. I am also currently enrolled at ECU in the Masters of Nursing program for nursing education. I have a 3.6 GPA and have taken 18 credit hours this year. I plan to graduate in December of 2017.', 'Agree with Mrs. Edges comments. &nbsp;', 'Student evaluations were discussed. &nbsp;Areas of concern were addressed and discussed with strategies for improvement.&nbsp;', 'Krystle Edge', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(18, 'Michele Moore', '2016-07-12', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'We are increasing the number students in our online certificate programs. Prospective students are calling from all over the state looking for online Spanish and online Spanish Interpreting courses.<p>Half of the students in our online Summer Spanish 3 (SPA211) class were university students (UNC, NC State, and UNCW) needing the class this summer. We created an online Spanish Placement Exam in Moodle so that prospective students can take the placement exam without having to come on campus.</p>', 'Mrs. Moore does a fantastic job managing all those students and classes as a single person dept. &nbsp;DM', 'I completed DBA110 this Spring with Mr. Wiggins, thus completing the requirements for my Web Design Certificate. I completed DFT119 this summer with Mr. Grady. I have been accepted in the PhD Instructional Design for Online Learning at Capella University. I have completed one class, and will have completed another by the time school starts again this fall.<p><br></p><p>I am currently taking Camtasia tutorials to learn how to perfect grammar videos for my online students.</p>', 'Mrs. Moore has completed the required hours. DM', 'Michele does a phenomenal job as dept chair for SPI as well as instructor for all the SPA courses on campus. &nbsp;She consistently has the highest number of hours and students, yet does a fantastic job always. &nbsp;DM', 'Michele Moore', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(19, 'Benita Hayes', '2016-07-11', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'I have continued to supervise and maintain the Office Administration and Medical Office Administration department. Served on the realignment committee for the adoption of the new Office Administration tracks that will be effective starting Fall 2017 on the system office level. Managed distribution of certification vouchers for student Microsoft Office certifications.Taught appropriate course load as needed per semester. Advised students during New Student Orientation sessions and returning students.', 'Benita has done a great job increasing enrollment in her program as well as managing the OA/MOA programs. DM', 'Will continue to seek professional development workshops offered for interpersonal and soft skills. Attended a training session on the use of MindTap to be used with Fall 2016 courses. Completed 48 hours of WEB 110 course. Continuing to take courses to prep for Medical Coding and Billing Certification.', 'Benita has met the required hours. DM', 'I am pleased with Benitas efforts as OA/MOA dept. chair. &nbsp;She and her staff has increasingly tried new methods to increase enrollment, as well been willing to teach in other departments as needed. &nbsp;DM', 'Benita Faye Hayes', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(20, 'Kristina Edwards', '2016-07-12', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '<p>Goal 1; Objective 1.3 - Goal met. I have been able to advise students, providing appropriate data to allow them to select appropriate courses to promote completion of their courses. </p><p><br></p><p>Goal 4; Objective 4.1 - Goal met. I have participated in ACEN committee meetings to obtain data on learning outcomes and program outcomes.</p><p><br></p><p>Goal 4; Objective 4.3 - Goal met. Student and institutional data was utilized in the decision making process to assist with improving retention and student outcomes. </p>', 'Agree with Mrs. Edwards self-evaluation. &nbsp;She has satisfactorily met her performance objectives as stated and her job duties as outlined.&nbsp;', 'Goal partially met. I have continued to research and provide car utilizing best practices through my employment as a staff nurse; however, I was unable to maintain my ACLS and PALS certifications. There were no classes offered through my employer at a time I could attend. I have maintained by CPR certification. I was unable to attend a test item writing workshop. I did attend a very informative concept-based curriculum workshop with the entire nursing faculty. Thisworkshop has provided me with a lot of information on how to help my students in the classroom and clinical setting.The LPN facultyhave already began to implement changes in our clinical paperwork based on the knowledge gained at this workshop. ', 'Agree with self-evaluation.&nbsp;', 'Mrs. Edwards student evaluations as a clinical and didactic instructor are positive. &nbsp;She is well-respected by the students. &nbsp;She is dependable and always willing to go the extra mile for the students and the department.&nbsp;', 'Kristina C. Edwards', 'Wanda H. Capps '),
(21, 'Edith Rogers', '2016-07-12', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '1, I have mastered basic copier operations and will continue studying the manuals to become proficient in utilizing other functions. I continue to perform periodic routine maintenance to ensure the machine operates at maximum efficiency.<p><br></p><p>2, I am comfortable using basic features of the phone system and would like to continue this objective by studying the Reference Guide in order to learn other features, including more effective use of the directory, using temporary external messages, etc.</p><p><br></p><p>3. I successfully completed transcript evaluations for this years departmental graduates. I would like to continue this objective because maintaining up-to-date files/program checklists promotes effective student advisement.</p>', 'There is ABSOLUTELY no way our division would function as efficiently and effectively without Edith and her guidance and knowledge. &nbsp;DM', 'Membership in the NCAEOP has expired for this year and is due for renewal. I plan to renew membership in the organization for 2016-2017.<p><br></p><p>I did not attend the NCAEOP meetings/ conferences as planned this year and missed several workshop/seminar opportunities. Consequently, I did not participate in as many professional development activities as I would have liked to. I completed the new DMS (developmental math) shells tutorials and can assist faculty and students during registration periods.</p><p><br></p><p>I have not completed any (CE) courses due to time constraints; however, I will be more proactive in seeking relevant professional development activities.</p>', 'Edith has completed the required hours. DM', 'Edith Rogers is a wonderful person and an extraordinary employee. &nbsp;She does a fantastic job as division secretary and is always willing to pull other duties if needed. &nbsp;We are fortunate to have her as part of our division. &nbsp;DM', 'Edith A. Rogers', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(22, 'Wanda H Capps', '2016-07-13', '2015-2016', 'bstarling@sampsoncc.edu', 'Performance objectives 1, 2, 4, and 5 have been met as stated.&nbsp;<p><br></p><p>Performance objective #3 - "Begin process for establishing a Medical Assistant program" has been exceeded in that the program has been approved and will begin Fall 2016. &nbsp;The process was also completed and approved to offer the EMS curriculum beginning Fall 2016.&nbsp;</p><p>Data for all nursing options is evaluated and trended as stated.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'I continue to serve as a site evaluator for ACEN and SACS. &nbsp;I attend one site visit Fall of 2015 and will be serving as an ACEN evaluator Fall 2016. &nbsp;I have attended all of the ADN directors meetings as well as two of the Deans of Health Sciences meetings. &nbsp;I met all of the other objective for professional training and development as stated.&nbsp;', '', '', 'Wanda H. Capps', ''),
(23, 'Robin Bradshaw', '2016-07-13', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1.Required and non required changes were implemented. Some worked well and some need some adjusting but we have worked on some things to implement this fall that will hopefully benefit the students.<p>Goal 1, Obj 1.5.<p><br></p><p>2 .I continue to collect data reflecting the passage rates and I have been able to identify some things that could be implemented to aid the students in the testing process which leads to the ultimate goal of    increased test scores. Goal 4, OBJ 4.1</p><p>3.I think the lab has been well maintained to meet the Division of Health Service Regulation Standards<br></p></p><p> Goal4</p>', 'Agree with Mrs. Bradshaws self-evaluation. &nbsp;She has met her goals and objectives as stated.&nbsp;', 'I have attended all Nurse Aide Regional Training session that have been offered.<p><br></p><p>I have attend more than required continuing education for professional development.</p>', 'Mrs. Bradshaw stays abreast and current with issues, changes, rules and regulations affecting the Nurse Aide courses. &nbsp;She also serves as coordinator and communicates those to the Continuing Education Division.&nbsp;', 'Mrs. Bradshaw is truly a team player not only for Nurse Aide and Phlebotomy but for the entire Health Programs DIvision. &nbsp;She has been essential in keeping the area running smoothly in the absence of an Administrative Assistant and offers herself to our newly employed Administrative Assistant in orienting her to her job.&nbsp;', 'Robin Bradshaw', 'Wanda H Capps '),
(24, 'Veronica F. Stevens', '2016-07-14', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Objective #1 was met. Quality instruction was provided, and academic excellence was fostered. 94% of students were successful in passing NCLEX-RN on the first writing.<p><br></p><p>2. Objective #2 was met. Innovative learning opportunities were developed and facilitated. An online option for LPN to ADN students was sucessfully delivered. 100% of those students successfully passed     NCLEX-RN. Innovative strategies were used in face to face and online options to deliver course content.</p><p><br></p><p>3. Objective #3 was met. Data was collected and maintained for ACEN accreditation. The program had a successful focused site visit from our accrediting agency in April of 2016.</p><p><br></p><p>4. Efforts to continue to increase retention through advising, counseling and effective teaching continue. Retention for Nursing 211 was 88% for 2015. Retention for NUR 114 was 93% for 2015. Retention for NUR 212 was 100% for 2015. Retention for NUR 213 was 100% for 2016. Retention for the online option was 44% for NUR 221 and 100% for NUR 223.</p>', 'Dr. Stevens has excelled as always in meeting her goals and professional objectives she sets. &nbsp;Her efforts to increase retention are directly related to her commitment to the students and the time she spends with them to assist them in understanding and grasping the information. Job well-done!&nbsp;', 'I received a Doctorate of Nursing Practice in December of 2015.', 'Agree with self-evaluation. &nbsp;Dr. Stevens accomplished her goal while attending as a full-time status student and continuing to work full-time. &nbsp;Never once were the students needs not met.&nbsp;', 'Dr. Stevens truly enjoys what she does and the impact she has upon students and their success speaks for itself. She is always willing to do extra and stays for students not matter the amount of time needed. A true definition of dedication and a team player.&nbsp;', 'Veronica F. Stevens', 'Wanda H. Capps ');
INSERT INTO `perfobj3` (`ID`, `employee`, `date_submitted`, `obj_setting_period`, `supervisor`, `section_1_employee`, `section_1_supervisor`, `section_2_employee`, `section_2_supervisor`, `evaluation_summary`, `employee_signature`, `supervisor_signature`) VALUES
(25, 'Julia Amanda Bradshaw', '2016-07-25', '2015-2016', 'abutler@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">1. &nbsp;<i>Offer a minimum of 55 seminars for the 2015-2016fiscal year and increase the number of SBC clients to a minimum of 60. Striveto increase average seminar attendance to compare with state average of 11.8.</i><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><i><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:blue">Completed 67 seminars witha total attendance of 632. Average attendance per seminar was 9.43 persons. Abit below my desired goal of 11.8, but overall very pleased with the quality ofbusiness owners that were in attendance. Successfully signed on 67 new clientsthis year for the SBC.</span></i><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Comic Sans MS&quot;;">2. &nbsp;</span></i><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Partnerwith the NC Military Business Center to investigate possible county businessesthat could qualify to apply for federal contracts. LaNell Grissom and myselfwill work together to register the businesses into the Federal E-ProcurementSystem. LaNell will then work to find possible contract possibilitiesnationwide to increase business in Sampson County.</span></i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><i><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:blue">Was able to partner withLaNell Grissom of the NCMBC. She and I met with several potential candidatebusinesses that we felt could best meet the needs of the Federal Government. 2have decided to start the Federal registration process. This process is verylengthy and takes several months to complete for most businesses. We arecurrently working with them by way of one-on-one appointments and via emailsupport. Our hopes are to get this process completed this year and to assistboth companies in procuring those contracts. Once their registration process iscomplete, we will try to locate 2 more that fitthe&nbsp;qualified&nbsp;standards necessary.</span></i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><i><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:blue"><br></span></i></p><p class="MsoListParagraph" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;margin-left:13.5pt;mso-add-space:auto;text-indent:-13.5pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><!--[if !supportLists]--><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Comic Sans MS&quot;;">3.<span style="font-style: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp; </span></i><!--[endif]--><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Create an improved communication web to betterreach a variety of clients thus extending the economic impact in the community.</span></i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">a.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Continuewith newsletter</span></i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br><i>b.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Continue to boost a social media presence for theSBC via Facebook and Google+</i><br><i>c.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Continue to use Constant Contact to reach clientson a more regular basis including several video series of interest for smallbusiness owner</i><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><i><br></i></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><i><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:blue">Communication effortshave tremendously improved over the year. I credit this communication effortwith the boost in seminar attendees and a boost in client attendance. We willcontinue to use each of these methods this new year. Brandon Wiggins will berolling the SBC Facebook page into the SCC Facebook page in order to broadenthe reach of the current page. Also, in an effort to be more efficient with mytime and that of clients, a new online scheduling system. Acuity scheduling, isbeing used. After running a test for the month of June and July, the system isvery efficient and has&nbsp;received&nbsp;high marks from users. I plan to rollthis out and use for the entire year of 2016-2017.&nbsp;</span></i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">4. Film, produce andadvertise the SBC using current and past seminar attendees via advertisementson the SCC Star Communications channel. Goal: (6) 2-3 minute commercials withsmall business owners.</span></i><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Comic Sans MS&quot;;"><o:p></o:p></span></i></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:-.25in"><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></i><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:blue">This goal was accomplished with filming taking place at 5 SampsonCounty Businesses during the summer of 2015 and released through out the fallof 2015. Each owner has used the promotional to bring light to their businessand the need for content on the SCC channel was filled. We are currentlyfilming 3 more for a fall release. Dan Grubbs and myself worked as an awesometeam to build solid 3-4 minute promotional opportunities that reflect thebusiness and its products. Also, the videos shine a bright light upon theclose relationship with the SBC into the public and as an ultimate reflectionof SCC.</span><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:-.25in"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:-.25in"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;5.&nbsp;<i>Partner with the Downtown ClintonPlanning Board, Clinton-Sampson Chamber of Commerce and the SBC to build a morerobust campaign for Small Business Saturday on November 28, 2015</i></span><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Comic Sans MS&quot;;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; .</span></i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:blue">A successful partnershipwas indeed formed to help promote Small Business Saturday, not only in Clinton,but across Sampson County. The Clinton&nbsp;Main Street&nbsp;Committee,Clinton-Sampson Chamber of Commerce and the&nbsp;Western-Sampson Commerce Groupeach helped to spread the word across news media, social media media andthrough the local businesses themselves. A seminar was held to help businessesprep and offered up marketing materials. Plans area already under way to helppromote this years event.&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:-.25in"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Comic Sans MS&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Comic Sans MS&quot;;">6.&nbsp;</span></i><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Continue- Offer seminars that are more supportive to current students of SampsonCommunity College and exploring the idea of becoming a business owner with theeducation acquired at SCC.&nbsp; (Example: Welding, Construction,&nbsp;Cosmetology)Have scheduled a class with the cosmetology department for the fall semester<o:p></o:p></span></i></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:-9.0pt"><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></i><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Comic Sans MS&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:blue">The SBC did offer several seminars thatwere structured to support the needs of Cosmetology and Welding department.Each was well attended and plan to continue to hold these during the Spring of2017.</span><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:-.25in"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:-9.0pt"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp; &nbsp; 7.<i>&nbsp;Create and begin a networking sessiontitled B2B OpenMeet as an opportunity to help small business owners get freeadvice and suggestions from other small business owners and business peers fromwithin the community. Will partner with James Sprunt Community College SBC forAugust-December on the 1</i></span><i><sup><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot;Comic Sans MS&quot;;">st</span></sup></i><i><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;Wednesday of each month. Will decideafter that point if program is strong enough to continue.<o:p></o:p></span></i></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent:-9.0pt"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:blue">&nbsp;I am very proud tosay that we did accomplish this goal with great success. The group that hasemerged from these sessions are much stronger business owners and betterconnected after learning from one another in recent months. These seems to be asense of relief from the participating business owners in knowing that they aresupported by the SBC and by the support of fellow business owners. In movingforward this year, we will not have the participation of the JSCC SBC due tolack of participation but will happily accept any referrals as he finds them.Also, we will be having some sessions in the Downtown Clinton area and othersin the Downtown Roseboro area (the local mayor and leaders are excited to havethis partnership).</span><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">-Graduated with a Masters in Education in Training and Development in May of2016.</span><span style="font-size:12.0pt;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">- Attended Intro. toHootsuite for Small Business Owners (October 9th) - 3 hours<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">- Attended BrandingDos and Donts for Small Business Owners (October 22) - 3 hours<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">- Attended SBCN/SBTDCJoint Fall Professional Development Conference (November 3-5) - 15 hours<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">- Attended DealingWith Difficult People (November 19th) - 2 hours<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">- Attended SBCNProfessional Development (March 9-11) - 15 hours<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '', '', 'Julia Amanda Bradshaw', ''),
(26, 'Sabrina Pope ', '2016-07-25', '2015-2016', 'wcapps@sampsoncc.edu', '1. Increase student retention through quality counseling, advising, and instruction (Goal 1, Objective 1.1).<p><br></p><p>2. Develop innovative learning opportunities to assess students and improve student outcomes (Goal Objective 1.5).</p><p><br></p><p>3. Expand opportunities for student engagement with staff and faculty (Goal 1, Objective 4).</p><p><br></p><p>4. Participate in assessments to identify and meet community needs to promote open access to the college (Goal 3, Objective 3.3).</p><p><br></p><p>5. Collect data to maintain ACEN accreditation (Goal 4)</p><p><br></p>', 'Agree with Ms. Popes self-evaluation. &nbsp;She has met all performance objectives as stated and continues to work toward more goals in her role as an educator, advisor and clinical instructor.&nbsp;', 'I will continue to enhance my development by attending and participating in learning activities, such as available workshops or seminars. I will continue to participate in campus and department committees as well as any community committees.', 'Mrs. Pope completed her MSN degree in June 2016. &nbsp;She researches evidence-based practices related to nursing education and shares with the faculty.&nbsp;', 'Ms. Pope is a team player who will be the first to jump in when there is a need for something to be done or a co-worker needs assistance. &nbsp;SCC is fortunate to have her as part of the nursing team!&nbsp;', 'Sabrina Pope, MSN, RN', 'WandaH Capps'),
(27, 'Lisa Horne', '2016-08-02', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', 'Continue to assist the Occupational Faculty as needed with handouts, student registering, computer problems etc.<p>I have learned a lot working with the new version of Moodle. I have become pretty efficient with the program.</p><p>Remained a Notary Public for students, staff and faculty.</p><p>I strive to promote a friendly campus atmosphere and be as helpful as I can to visitors, students, faculty and staff.</p>', 'Lisa Horne, with her typical job requirements, manages her time and resources very well. &nbsp;She is always willing to assist our division. &nbsp;WDM', 'I have attended the following training sessions at SCC since my Progress Conference Form #2:<p><br></p><p><ul><li>Cross Training: Computer Surplus - January 28, 2016</li><li>Cross Training: Computer Surplus - January 29, 2016</li><li>Cross Training: Computer/Misc. Surplus - February 1, 2016</li><li>Cross Training: Surplus Paperwork - February 17, 2016</li><li>Cross Training: Surplus Misc./Library Items - February 19, 2016</li><li>Cross Training: Surplus Misc./Library Items - February 22, 2016</li><li>Cross Training: Transferring Computers, etc. - April 13, 2016</li><li>Cross Training: Transferring Student Desks - July 28, 2016</li></ul></p>', 'Lisa has completed the necessary hours. &nbsp;WDM', 'Lisa Horne has assisted me and the Occupational division faculty with any needs they may have. &nbsp;She is a valuable asset. &nbsp;WDM', 'Lisa Horne', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(28, 'Vicky Williams', '2016-05-03', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman, serif;">I have continued to learn considerable knowledge aboutthe new ICD-10 Coding bytakinga ICD-10 course in Continuing Education.I will also obtainmy AHIMAState  Certification in ICD-10Coding, which will allow me to teach students on an advancedlevel that will allow students tochallenge AHIMA state board to obtain state certification  in ICD-10 Coding.</span>', 'Mrs. Williams has completed the courses and certifications needed for her MOA instruction. DM', '<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman, serif;">I have obtained substantial knowledge thru sessionstaken at the conference and webinars  tobetter my teaching techniques. I havealso learned great deal of knowledge thru the ICD-10 Course taken in the Continuing Education department at Sampson CommunityCollege that will allow me to help me toprepare future students in the MOA program inobtaining their AHIMA certification in ICD-10 Coding.</span>', 'Mrs. Williams has completed the required hours. DM', 'Mrs. Williams is truly an asset to our OA/MOA programs. DM', 'Vicky Williams', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(29, 'Al Spraker', '2016-06-30', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">1. In the Fall Semester I taught NET 225 and NET226 which are the Cisco Netacad Semester3 and 4 courses. These courses helpprepare the students for the CCNA exam.Net 125 and 126 which is also taguth prepares students for the CCENTexam. The new courses also included objectives that are on the new Version 5(Routing and Switching exam) <o:p></o:p></span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">2. Nathan McKee was hired this spring as a CIT/ISSinstructor and has done really well fitting in. We work extremely well together team teaching the CTS 289 and SEC289 Courses. <o:p></o:p></span></u></p><u><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA;layout-grid-mode:line">3 . Server 2008 was taught in both the NOS 130and NOS 230 courses this year but we will be full adopting Server 2012 with anew textbook this fall.</span></u>', 'Als knowledge and expertise in network security are second to none. &nbsp;He brings a great amount of experience and vigor to the classroom. &nbsp;We are fortunate to have him as our lead IT Security instructor. &nbsp;DM', '<p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">1. Icomplete well over the required 15 professional development hours and did notrecord many additional hours that I had to put in to maintain my skills.<o:p></o:p></span></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u><span style="font-family:"Times New Roman",serif">2. I recertifiedmy CCNA and CCNA Security in April by taking the CCNP Routing andSwitching Route exam. I received a scoreof 904 out of 1000 on the exam. I hopeto continue studying for the CCNP Switch exam later this summer and take thefinal TShoot exam this fall. The nexttwo exam will complete the requirements for the CCNP certification. <o:p></o:p></span></u></p><u><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA;layout-grid-mode:line">3. I attended theStatewide Cisco Academy Conference inMarch and had the opportunity to collaborate with many Cisco AcademyInstructors from other college and universities in developing methods topresent network concepts to ourstudents.</span></u>', 'Al has completed the required 15 hours of professional development. &nbsp;DM', 'Al is an excellent instructor, faculty member, and advisor to our students. &nbsp;His experience, both life and professional, lends itself well to the overall instruction of our students. &nbsp;DM', 'Al Spraker', 'W. Darell Matthews'),
(30, 'Nathan McKee', '2016-05-04', '2015-2016', 'dmatthews@sampsoncc.edu', '<p class="MsoNormal"><u>1. I have completed instruction of the CTS120, SEC110,NOS130, and CTS289 Courses for Spring 2016. <o:p></o:p></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u>2. I have identified the need for and implemented (3)hands-on workstation carts for use in the CTS-120 course to allow studentsadditional access to training resources while in the course   3. The CTS-120 courseplanned and built a computer for use as an ESXi server, demo for hardware RAID, as well as troubleshootingscenarios. <o:p></o:p></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u>4. During the Spring 2016 semester I worked as theComputer Club Advisor and plan to help expand its activities in futuresemesters.<o:p></o:p></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u>5. I implemented new Final Exams for CTS120 and SEC110that focus heavily on hands-on work by students.<o:p></o:p></u></p><u><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA;layout-grid-mode:line">6. After completing theCisco IT Essentials course during Summer 2016, I plan on implementing much ofthat course material to future CTS120 courses.</span></u>', 'Nathan has proved to be an excellent resource and instructor for our department and our students. &nbsp;DM', '<p class="MsoNormal"><u>1. I attended the CISCO Conference at Stanly CommunityCollege on 3/8/16 (8 hours)  2. I completed five courses onPluralsight.com related to Security+ (17.5hours)<o:p></o:p></u></p><p class="MsoNormal"><u>3. I completed the CompTIA Security+ CertMaster coursetotaling (10 Cont. Edu. Hours) 4. I begin the Cisco IT Essentials and CCNAIntro to Networking courses on 5/24/165. I am scheduled to take the CompTIA Security+ exam on 5/12/16<o:p></o:p></u></p><u><span style="font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA;layout-grid-mode:line">6. I will continue to improveIT knowledge and course prep throughout the summer</span></u>', 'Nathan has completed the required number of professional development hours. &nbsp;DM', 'Nathan McKee has proved himself as a wonderful instructor. &nbsp;His knowledge and experience are always appreciated by our students. &nbsp;He is always willing to help and do what it takes to bring our department to the community. &nbsp;DM', 'Nathan McKee', 'W. Darell Matthews');
